title: six can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Pour half of
sauce
over
loaf.
Bake
at
350° for 45 minutes.
Add remaining sauce; baste often.
Bake an additional 45 minutes.
This
can be made into two loaves.
it freezes well. Freeze loaf without sauce and add sauce when used.

title: pear relish
directions: Place pears, onions, bell pepper, hot pepper, salt, mustard, allspice, sugar and vinegar in a pot and boil for 1 hour on low temperature.

title: lemon-flavored potato salad
directions: About 45 minutes before serving or early in day:
In a 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepan over high heat, heat unpeeled potatoes and enough water to cover to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Drain; cool potatoes until easy to handle.
Peel and cut potatoes into bite size chunks.

title: strawberry cheese cake pie(diet)
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in Sugar Twin or Equal.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into dish.
Chill until set.
Arrange fresh strawberries, hulled and halved, on filling.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon mixture on a greased cookie sheet.
Not too close together, cookies will spread and are very thin.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and beef in shortening in skillet.
Add tomatoes, ketchup, steak sauce, pepper and parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni.
Mix macaroni with beef in baking dish.
Season to taste. Gently spoon soup into mixture.
Mix lightly and sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mustang tire doughnuts
directions: These are nice and soft and do not soak fat.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: In a large skillet cook sausage thoroughly.
Break up sausage while cooking.
Drain and allow to cool.

title: appetizer franks
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine the tomato sauce, water, vinegar, spaghetti sauce mix, sugar and dry mustard.
Stir in hot dogs until coated.
Microwave, covered, until heated through, about 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir twice.

title: creamed onions and peas
directions: Blend soup and milk
in saucepan. Add peas, onions and pepper. Heat gently, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: greek spinach-cheese pie
directions: Chop spinach.
Saute minced onion in olive oil until transparent.
Add spinach; cover and cook until most of moisture evaporates.
Remove from heat; add dill, nutmeg, salt, pepper, cottage cheese, Feta cheese, chopped onion and eggs.
Mix well. Combine wheat germ and melted butter.
Press into bottom and sides of large, flat baking dish.
Pour cheese-spinach mixture into dish, spreading evenly.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until crisp and brown.
Slice to serve.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add sugar gradually.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and fold into egg mixture.
Add vanilla; fold dates and nuts into batter.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into one by two-inch bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: roast beef and sunday potatoes
directions: In Dutch oven, sear meat on both sides.
Sear until well darkened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients except for potatoes and carrots.
Cook at 350° until meat is done. Add potatoes and carrots and bake until vegetables are tender.

title: aunt teddie's delicious salad
directions: Layer in large bowl. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 or up to 8 hours.
Mix just before serving.

title: buttermilk sausage pinwheel biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour. Add buttermilk; mix.
Knead on floured board.
Roll into rectangle. Spread sausage over dough. Roll up jelly roll style. Chill several hours or overnight.
Cut, seam side down, into individual biscuits.
Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for 25 minutes. Serve with eggs for breakfast.

title: curried chicken
directions: Mix together to make sauce the honey, mustard, soy sauce and curry. Dip chicken in sauce to coat well.
Place in foil lined pan. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes. Turn over and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: layered salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach.
Tear spinach in small pieces and place in bottom of large salad bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Add bacon, eggs, lettuce, peas, onion and chicken in separate layers.

title: swedish meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl with wet hands.
Shape mixture into a loaf in a shallow ungreased baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven about 1 hour or until brown.

title: sole with garlic sauce
directions: In a small frying pan, melt 3 tablespoons butter over medium-low heat.
Add garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until garlic just begins to turn golden (15 minutes). Remove from heat and keep warm. Rinse fish and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda in large bowl. Add oil and eggs; mix thoroughly. Stir in strawberries, pineapple and pecans. Pour batter into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Wrap loaves tightly in foil overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring the soup and milk to a boil and add 1/2 pound of Velveeta cheese and the garlic salt.
Stir until melted.
Pour over the broccoli, rice and sauteed onion.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: citrus punch
directions: Combine citric acid and 1 cup of cold water; refrigerate overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes 5 quarts of punch and serves 25 people.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done; reserve stock.
Take meat off bones. Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add flour, stirring until smooth; do not brown.
Add whipping cream and chicken stock, stirring constantly, so mixture will not lump.
Add mushrooms, pimento, chicken and salt.
Simmer for about 4 or 5 minutes.
Serve on hot toast, English muffins, rice or Chinese noodles.

title: banana-orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine/butter and sugar together.
Add sour cream, flour, 3 eggs and salt.
Squeeze orange juice through strainer.
Add mashed banana and orange juice to batter; mix well.
Pour batter into lightly greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until browned.
Makes approximate serving for 14.

title: irish lamb stew
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery and turnips in a microwave bowl.
Cook, covered, on High for 10 minutes.
Remove and let stand.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, sugar, salt, soda and margarine.
Divide mixture in half.
Use 1/2 for bottom crust.
Pat into pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and milk.
Spread this on baked crust and sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top. Top with remaining crust mixture.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
In large mixing bowl, combine wheat germ, nuts, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Form a well and add eggs, pumpkin and melted shortening or salad oil.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery in oleo until tender and soft, not
brown.
Add flour and mix well.
Add other ingredients; mix well
and
cook
on
low
for 2 hours.
Add 3 pounds shrimp that have
been	peeled and deveined.
Cook slowly for another hour.

title: southern fried apple rings
directions: Mix sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Slice apples in 1/2-inch slices.
Heat butter in heavy frying pan.
Add apple rings and 1/2 of sugar mixture; cook about 3 minutes.
Turn. Sprinkle with remainder of sugar mixture.
Continue cooking until apples are almost transparent.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bloody mary mix
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Excellent for the morning after!

title: tonti's pecan puffs(sheryl little's mother)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites (high speed) until soft peaks form.
Sprinkle sugar, a few tablespoons at a time.
Beat until completely dissolved.
Do not scrape bowl during beating!
Beat in vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on the cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: curry dip
directions: Make
night before.
Mix all ingredients and serve with various
vegetables
(carrots, celery, mushrooms, cauliflower, zucchini, peppers, etc.).

title: summer garden pizza
directions: Press crescent dough flat onto a jelly roll pan and bake according to directions, don't overbake.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, dried dill and minced onion and spread over baked crescent rolls.
Sprinkle all diced vegetables over the cream cheese mixture.
Pile as high as you like, then cut into small pieces and serve.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Combine cream cheese, soup and seasoned salt in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture is thoroughly heated, stirring often.
Pour over potatoes, mixing well.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and onion together until done.
Debone chicken while still warm and cut into small pieces.
Add eggs, pickles and allspice.
Mix well.
Blend mayonnaise with chicken mixture while still warm.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, salt, vanilla and sugar.
Add milk.
Stir.
Dip bread into mixture and brown on both sides on hot, lightly greased griddle.
Serve with maple syrup or jelly or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package directions and drain. Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Mix in small bowl, sour cream, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Add cheese and stir until blended.
Spray casserole with nonstick spray and add noodles, chicken and broccoli, then bow mixture and mix together in casserole dish.
You can add more cheese on top and breadcrumbs if you wish.
Also pour on little dollops of milk to moisten before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mushroom sauce(microwave)
directions: Micromelt butter on High 1 minute.
Saute onion, bouillon cube, garlic powder and pepper in butter.
Cook on High 8 minutes. Stir after 1/2 of cooking time.
Stir in flour; add water slowly. Add mushrooms and wine.
Cover.
Cook on High for 5 minutes. Sauce can be frozen and reheated.
Serves 6.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix well and let stand out of refrigerator all day, 8 to 10 hours.
This does not rise, only makes bubbles.
Take out 1 cup to make bread.
Return the rest to refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.
Repeat step 2.
Each time must feed and must remove 1 cup of the starter.
Keep covered in refrigerator only leave one corner of cover up.
I use foil and bend one corner back.

title: cocoa drops
directions: Bring to rolling boil the sugar, cocoa, oleo, milk and vanilla. Boil for 1 minute. Add oatmeal and peanut butter. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Cool.

title: microwave shrimp creole
directions: Saute first 6 ingredients in a 3-quart dish on High for 20 minutes or	until
wilted.	Stir
in
flour.
Add tomatoes, sauce and broth.	Cook
on
High	for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp. Cover and cook on
High 6 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Stir once or twice.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: spicy cajun chicken pesto
directions: In skillet with small amount of canola oil, cook chicken. While cooking, add Cajun spices.
In bowl, mix alfredo sauce and pesto sauce.
Cook mostaccioli as directed.
Combine all ingredients in large pan and heat.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Cook until carrots, onion and potatoes are tender.
Add smoked sausage.
Cook until sausage is thoroughly heated.

title: creamed dry beef
directions: Heat butter in skillet; add chopped dried beef and frizzle a few minutes.
Push to side of pan.
Add flour and stir (if too dry, add more butter) until flour turns a light brown.
Add milk until it's the thickness you like.
You can change the amount by using more or less flour and milk.
Also you can use less beef. Serve over homemade bread.
Delicious.

title: pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut flat into flour with a pastry fork (grandma used a spoon) until mixture is like coarse meal.
Add the water by teaspoon, mixing lightly.
Gather into a ball and roll out on floured board.
Makes one pastry shell.

title: chicken penne
directions: Cook the pasta according to the package directions.
Add the first 6 ingredients to a frying pan.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes until chicken is cooked through.
Drain the noodles and in a bowl mix with the tomato mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.
Serves 2 (can be doubled easily).

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1-quart loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Press into prepared pan.
Bake about 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookies(an all time favorite and easy to make.)
directions: Mix milk, butter, cocoa and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Let cool 1 minute.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: yogurt-gelatin delight(heart association)
directions: Prepare the fruit gelatin according to package directions. Chill until it begins to set.
Stir the yogurt in until thoroughly combined with the gelatin.
Return to refrigerator until set.

title: apple butter
directions: Core and chop apples (do not peel).
Combine apples and cider in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or until apples are mushy.
Puree in a food mill or sieve.
Return mixture to pot.
Add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Cover and cook on low 1 hour or more, until mixture is thickened.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for cornflake mixture. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cornflake mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: anise seed cookies
directions: Cream lard with sugar until fluffy.
Add anise seed.
Beat eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixer with 1/2 cup water.

title: layer salad
directions: Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Chill overnight.

title: solid chocolate cake
directions: Heat chocolate and milk.
Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add egg yolks. Add cool chocolate mixture.
Keep a little out of last cup of flour and add remaining and add baking powder.
Add stiffly beaten whites of eggs and vanilla.
Beat one way.

title: sugar-free strawberry cheesecake
directions: *3/4 c. no-sugar-added strawberry fruit spread combined with 1/4 cup warm water may be substituted.

title: baked potato spears
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into wedges.
Brush with Miracle Whip. Season with onion salt and pepper.
Place on a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan or just use a cookie sheet, whatever you have handy.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Serve with Parmesan Dip.

title: chocolate nut angel pie
directions: Sift sugar and Tartar together.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar gradually until glossy and smooth.	Grease Pie Pan.
Put in pan and around sides.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: yvette's bean dip
directions: Cook hamburger meat with chopped onions.
Drain fat; add 1/2 of taco sauce mix with 1/4 cup water.
Add refried beans and mix. Add chopped tomatoes.
Grate cheese and add 3/4 of it to the mixture.
Cook over medium-low heat and stir until bubbling.
Add remaining cheese on top.
Enjoy!!!

title: heavenly bliss dessert
directions: Cook and cool eggs, flour, sugar, margarine, pineapple juice and vanilla. Add together marshmallows, pineapple and cherries. Add cooled mixture to marshmallow mixture.
Add Cool Whip last when cold.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add onions and cook until tender. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
In an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, layer half of the noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese, Velveeta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onion and red pepper.
Cover with salt. Let stand overnight.
In morning, drain and wash off salt.
Add sugar, turmeric, mustard seed and horseradish.
Cover with vinegar and heat to boiling point.
Turn into clean jars and seal.
Makes 2 pints.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Put Crisco shortening and butter in a large bowl and soften. Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well with a spoon and set in refrigerator.

title: chocolate cinnamon mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool and frost with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: hamburger and barley pot
directions: Lightly brown meat in margarine, breaking it up as it cooks. Add onion and cook 5 more minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except barley.
Bring to a boil.
Add barley and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until barley is tender.
Uncover for the last 15 minutes of cooking to reduce liquid.

title: chocolate cream frosting
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 cup sugar, butter, Choco Bake, vanilla and salt; beat until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Alternately blend in remaining confectioners sugar and milk.
Continue beating at medium speed until thick enough to spread.
Fills and frosts 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake layers.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1 cup stuffing to top. Put in 13 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch baking dish. Top with reserved stuffing. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Melt oleo, add sugar and milk; bring to a boil.
Cook 6 minutes.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir until cool. Spread in buttered pan.
Makes a large amount.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and 1 egg and press into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan. Combine remaining ingredients. Spread over first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Cool. Cut in squares. Serve.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In a Dutch oven, put chicken, water and 2 teaspoons salt. Cover and boil.
Reduce heat; add pepper, onion and celery leaves. Simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken, onion and celery leaves.
Cool chicken, then skin, bone and cut into pieces.
Set aside.
Boil broth.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Add milk until ingredients are moistened.
Turn onto floured board. Knead lightly.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Drop into boiling broth.
Turn heat to low and cook 10 minutes.
Stir gently.
Stir in chicken and heat.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix all together.
Grease Pyrex pan (that fits in microwave). Cook 2 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 1 or 2 minutes more until melted. Remove from oven.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add 1 cup walnuts or pecans (cut up).
Put in refrigerator until set.
Cut in small squares.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar. Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip; pour in crust.
Cover with peanuts.
Freeze until firm.
Put under stove broiler until it bubbles.

title: chicken creole
directions: In a Dutch oven, boil chicken until done.
Cool and remove chicken from bones.
Reserve liquid.
In a 4-quart saucepan heat oil; add onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in canned tomatoes, 3 cups of reserved chicken broth and remaining ingredients except rice; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Prepare and bake the cake mix using the package directions for a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Poke holes in the cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour the cream of coconut over the cake.
Top with whipped topping and coconut.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 15 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: In a large bowl, stir together refried beans, taco sauce and several dashes bottled hot pepper sauce, if desired.
Spread the refried beans mixture evenly on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bread pudding
directions: Arrange 3 biscuits or 3 slices of slightly stale bread on bottom of baking dish.
Mix milk, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour mixture over bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top for added flavor.

title: cheesy oven fries
directions: Wash potatoes well and cut each one into 8 wedges.
Set aside. Combine cheese and next 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Dip potato wedges in melted butter and roll in cheese mixture.
Arrange in single layer on lightly greased sheet pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and browned.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing at medium speed on mixer.
Blend well.
Put in center of a round tray or divided dish.
Place fruits around dip.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: savory sausage and rice casserole
directions: Lightly brown sausage in Dutch oven and pour off excess fat. Add celery, green pepper and onion and saute until tender.
Combine soup mix and boiling water in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in rice and cover; simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add rice mixture to sausage and stir well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Serves 10.

title: german chocolate snakin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate with margarine.
Remove from heat, stir in 1/2 cup Eagle Brand milk, eggs, Bisquick mix and vanilla.
Spread evenly into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and then cut up.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue beef on buns
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery in table fat.
Add salt.
Then add sauce.
Serve with a 2 ounce serving scoop on open face buns.

title: strawberry sparkle punch
directions: Puree strawberries in blender (strain to remove seed). Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade concentrate. Add mixture with strawberries to punch bowl.
Add cranberry cocktail and cold water.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Garnish with fresh strawberries or ice ring with whole berries frozen in.

title: bacon and cheddar quiche(it's quick and easy with pizza crust mix.)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease generously a deep 10-inch pie pan.
Mix pizza crust mix with water according to package directions.
After dough rests for 5 minutes, press into prepared pan and flute edges.
Bake crust for 5 minutes. Remove from oven; reduce temperature to 350°.
Sprinkle crust with bacon and cheese. Combine cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over bacon and cheese. Return to oven and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together in large bowl.
Mix and add the shortening, milk, chopped nuts, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well and pour into 4 (1 pound) coffee cans that have been greased and floured.
Fill coffee cans half full.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic, then drain off fat and let cool. Stir in cheese, crumbs, parsley, egg, salt, pepper and Mozzarella cheese.
Cook shells in boiling water and 1 tablespoon of oil and salt until almost tender, approximately 15 minutes.
Drain and stuff shells.
Pour small amount of sauce on bottom of casserole dish (9 x 13 x 2-inches).
Lay shells and mix wine with remaining sauce and pour over top of shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in preheated oven at 400° approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour gradually.
Stir in chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add yogurt and green chili peppers.
Roll chicken, 1 tablespoon sauce, cheese and onions in tortillas; place in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with cooking oil or spray.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas; sprinkle with cheese and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mickey's chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, gravy, green pepper, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Arrange the macaroni on top of the chicken mixture.
Dot with little pieces of the butter and sprinkle with the cheese. Cover and bake for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake for an additional 10 minutes.

title: vegetable minestrone soup for a crowd
directions: You will need a 6-quart pot.

title: white bean soup
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in a large saucepan; mash slightly with a potato masher.
Stir in water and cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Saute onion and carrot in butter until onion is tender.
Add sauteed vegetables and ham to bean mixture.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 1 quart.

title: pasta fritters
directions: Coarsely chop cooked spaghetti; set aside.
In small saucepan over medium heat in 1 tablespoon oil, cook green onions until tender.
In medium bowl, mix flour, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, egg and 1/4 cup water.
Stir in green onions and spaghetti until well coated.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil until very hot in a nonstick skillet.
Into hot oil, drop mixture by 1/4 cups into 4 mounds, about 2 inches apart.
With pancake turner, flatten each mound slightly.
Cook fritters until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions and drain.
Mix together soups, sauce and milk.
Line baking pan alternately with tortillas, sauce, meat and grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: brunch omelet
directions: Mix ingredients in dish.
Refrigerate 12 hours before baking in well buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 35 minutes.
Check in 25 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Sprinkle bacon on bottom of pie crust.
Saute onions in bacon drippings; place onions over bacon.
Sprinkle cheese over onion layer; add layer of spinach.
Beat together eggs and half and half.
Season with salt and pepper; pour over pie.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 45 to 50 minutes or until custard is set.
Let set for a few minutes before serving.

title: creole-stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash green peppers; cut a thin slice from stem end of each. Remove all seeds.
In a saucepan, boil peppers in boiling water with 1 1/4 teaspoons salt for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine chuck with onions, celery, 1 teaspoon salt, minced peppers, egg and cream.
Drain peppers; stuff with meat mixture.
Place stuffed peppers in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: fingerpainting "goop"
directions: Mix starch with enough cold water to make smooth paste.
Add boiling water and cook until glossy.
Stir in dry soap flakes while the mixture is warm.
Cool and pour into jars.
Will keep a week or longer if covered with tight lid.

title: cream of onion soup
directions: Boil together potatoes and onions.
Drain.
Save the water. Put vegetables through a coarse strainer.
Make a white sauce from the water, flour and butter.
Combine with the potato and onion pulp.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Beat with a mixer and serve with croutons.

title: easy breakfast eggs
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Place bread on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the rest of the ingredients over the bread and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Remove.
Add flour, salt, and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in milk and bring to boil for 1 minute.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: an apple smile
directions: Core and slice an apple.
Spread peanut butter on one side of each apple slice.
Place four tiny marshmallows on top of the peanut butter of one slice.
Top with another apple slice, peanut butter side down.
Gently squeeze together.

title: crab appetillas
directions: Mix
ingredients
together.
Put
1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture on a flour tortilla.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap each roll in wax paper and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together margarine, cake mix, egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour this mixture over cake mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Add zucchini, basil, water and chicken base.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until very tender.
Remove from heat.
Beat soup with mixer for 1 to 2 minutes to break up zucchini.
Add cream.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with croutons, if desired.

title: layered dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over bottom of pan.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over the fruits; top with nuts.
Cut up margarine into small pieces or slices and sprinkle on top as evenly as possible.
Do not mix. Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour or until brown.
Cut into squares and serve warm or cool with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Add pumpkin and blend well. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Let cool completely before frosting.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies(great for christmas cookies.)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Set aside. Cream together butter and shortening and add cream cheese and sugar. Beat until fluffy. Add egg and vanilla, beat well. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Divide dough in half. Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Place chicken, celery, bell pepper and dill pickles on a chopping acrylic board and chop finely.
Add sweet pickles.
Place mixture in a large mixing bowl.
Add pimentos, mustard, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Chop boiled eggs and add to mixture. Cover and refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: almond roca
directions: Melt butter and margarine.
Add sugar.
Cook until lemon-colored and bubbly; stir constantly.
Add almonds; cook until lightly browned.
Stir constantly.
Pour onto foil-lined baking sheet.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of chocolate.
Let stand until melted, then spread.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the walnuts.
Invert onto foil.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate.
Spread when melted. Sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes. Add rest of ingredients and beat until fluffy. Put in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with marshmallows and brown 30 minutes.

title: italian hotdish(from the kitchen of "sewing with nancy")
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In large casserole dish, combine noodles, meat and sauce.
Mix well.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pastry-pie crust
directions: Mix 3 cups flour, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1 cup lard until crumbly. Beat 1 egg; add 3 tablespoons water and 2 tablespoons vinegar. Add to mixture. Refrigerate until ready to use. Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Layer in cookie sheet or baking dish in order listed.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 7 to 10 minutes.
Top with jalapeno peppers (chopped) and salsa.

title: san juan quiche
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil and use a pie crust or line with flour tortillas (no foil).
Cook up in frying pan the hamburger, onion, garlic, pepper, taco sauce, cumin and chili powder.

title: wild rice quiche
directions: Bake crust at 425° for 5 minutes. Remove from the oven and set aside. Reduce heat to 325°. In a skillet, saute Canadian bacon or ham and onion in butter until onion is tender. Spoon into the crust. Sprinkle with cheese and wild rice.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, cream and salt.
Pour over all. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Garnish with parsley, if desired. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cookie sundae
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and corn syrup in a mixing bowl.
Add peaches and mix well.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Slice cookie dough into 1/2-inch slices.
Place slices on top of peach mixture. Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cool and serve with ice cream, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in the boiling water and stir in the orange sherbet, stirring until dissolved.
Add the orange pieces and the pineapple.
Put in mold to congeal.

title: kristy's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown potatoes casserole(from southern living)
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup melted butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a greased, large, flat casserole dish.
Combine crushed cereal and remaining 1/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast
directions: Season with salt, pepper, Old Bay seasoning, Tabasco to taste.
Mix and serve over toast or biscuits.
May be made ahead and reheated.

title: basic cocktail sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve with cooked shrimp or other seafoods.
Recipe is enough to serve with 5 lbs. cooked shrimp. Can be frozen.

title: grandma kohn's carrot cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350°.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Cook 1/2 cup chopped onions in drippings until tender.
Cook ground beef or sausage in skillet. Drain fat.
Add all ingredients with beans and mix well.
Bake, uncovered in a 1 1/2-quart casserole at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: southern chocolate-mint brownies with mint cream frosting
directions: Beat eggs lightly with wire whisk in a large bowl.
Add sugar and stir well.
Combine flour and cocoa; gradually stir into egg mixture.
Stir in 1 cup butter and flavorings.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Spread Mint Cream Frosting over brownie layer; freeze 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate squares and 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring until melted.
Spread over frosting.

title: peanut butter bacon bread
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter, egg and butter.
Add alternately milk and dry ingredients. Mix well.
Add peanuts and bacon.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tuna jello salad
directions: Rinse
tuna
in
warm water;
break up and drain.
Dissolve jello
in
the boiling water.
Stir until dissolved and clear. Add
salt
and
lemon juice.
When cool, add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch lightly oiled casserole.	Refrigerate overnight.	Cut into squares and serve on lettuce
leaf
with
a sprig of mint, if desired.
(You may substitute	one lime or one orange jello for a different color scheme.)

title: small hungarian pastries
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter and salt like pie crust, then add egg yolks, sour cream and milk; knead well.
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick and cut into small squares.
Put a small amount of filling in center, then fold 2 corners on top, overlapping.
Brush with egg wash.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scottish mince and tatties
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in a large skillet with enough water to cover.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook for 20 minutes, covered.

title: rivel cake (coffee)
directions: Mix and squeeze lightly in fist (the lumps are the rivels) and then break into pieces and put into a pie plate.

Place pieces (about the size of a small walnut or hickory nut) in a square pan and bake at 325° to 350° until lightly brown or slightly hard. Serve in a cereal dish with hot coffee poured over it (seasoned as desired with milk and sugar).

title: refreshing chocolate soda
directions: Mix syrup and ginger ale in 12-ounce glass. Add ice cream and fill with soda. Makes 1 serving.

title: low-fat parmesan chicken
directions: Lightly salt chicken breasts and roll them in the mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Brown the breasts in the olive oil lightly.
Place the breasts in a Pam coated casserole dish and cover with the pasta sauce.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: feta tomato basil fish
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion and garlic in oil. Add tomatoes and basil. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes. Broil fish 4-6 inches from heat for 5 minutes. Top each piece of fish with tomato mixture and cheese. Broil 5-6 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, beans, chili powder, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole and line with tortillas.
Layer with meat mixture, tortillas and cheese. Spread mushroom soup over cheese.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over entire dish. Bake at 350° until bubbles, approximately 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain.
Add next eight ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Ready to serve.
Makes 1 quart.

title: wheat and lamb meat
directions: Cover meat and bones with water 4 to 5 inches above.
Add a little salt; bring to a boil.
Remove foam and cook until meat is tender.
Fry the onions in Crisco until transparent.
Add onions, spices, salt and chickpeas to meat and cook on low for 15 minutes. Remove 2 cups of broth with some onions and chickpeas to a small pan and save for sauce topping.
Wash cracked wheat, drain and add to meat and broth.
Broth should be about 1 inch above wheat. Cover and bring to a boil; boil briskly until water is level with wheat.
Lower heat and simmer until liquid is absorbed and wheat is done.
More broth can be added if needed.
Before completely dry, check for salt.
When done and dry, stir wheat to mix with meat and bones.
Serve on a deep platter.
Add some of the hot reserved broth with onions and chickpeas on top.
Serve with yoghurt.

title: frozen pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, nuts and spices.
Fold in softened vanilla ice cream.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Cover the bottom of the pan with 1/2 of the whole gingersnaps and press into the butter.
Layer with 1/2 of pumpkin/ice cream mixture. Repeat to form another layer of each.
Freeze overnight.

title: mixed greens
directions: Cut up and combine greens in a large Dutch oven.
Combine other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until done.

title: seafood salad
directions: Place shrimp and crab in large bowl.
Peel and cut eggs.
Add to seafood.
Cube bread slices.
Add to ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise into mixture and refrigerate.

title: autumn pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in slow cooker. Cover with apple juice. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover. Cook on low 10 hours.

title: easy stew, really e.a.s.y!
directions: Do not brown meat.
Place all in casserole.
Mix, cover and bake at 300° to 350° for 3 hours.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Chill lime, orange and cherry Jell-O until very firm.
Cut into small cubes.

title: bleu cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Grate Bleu cheese into cream cheese. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Great with hot wings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups of water until nearly done; remove from heat and add margarine; put in casserole dish and add onion soup, mushrooms, water chestnuts and liquid.
Bake in covered casserole 30 minutes in 350° oven.
May be done ahead of time and heated before serving.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Stuff pepper halves with mixture of remaining ingredients; put in shallow dish.
Pour 1 small can tomato sauce over peppers.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine fruits; set aside. In a small mixing bowl, beat pudding mix, milk and orange juice concentrate for 2 minutes. Add sour cream; mix well. Spoon pudding mixture over fruit; toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serves 8 -10.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix beaten eggs, corn, parsley, salt and pepper. Dissolve soda in 1 teaspoon warm water; add to corn mixture.
Add crumbs and shape into cakes.
Fry in deep fryer at 375° until golden brown. Drain.
Makes 12.

title: chicken and bean sprouts
directions: Simmer chicken until cooked through.
Remove from bone.
Drain artichokes and put in bottom of 1 1/2-quart greased casserole, then the chicken.
Salt to taste.
Drain bean sprouts and rinse in a large strainer under cold water.
Add to dish.
Mix soup and vermouth and spread over all.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 8-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
In a bowl, combine flour and remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbs form.
Drizzle water over apples.
Sprinkle with crumb topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until apples are tender.

title: individual coffee cakes
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Beat the egg and mix with milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir until blended.
Spoon into muffin tins with cupcake liners. Brush tops with melted butter.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Combine eggs, sugar and oil in separate bowl.
Beat well.
Stir in sifted ingredients well. Add pumpkin and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together confectioners sugar and peanut butter until it's coarse, crumbled mixture.
Beat egg yolks until fluffy.
Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch; beat into egg yolks.
Beat in hot milk gradually.
Cook over hot water until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Cover bottom of pie shell with 2/3 of peanut butter mixture.
Pour in the hot custard.

title: aunt mae's enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and onion, season with salt and pepper.
Add soups, green chiles and enchilada sauce.

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt, eggs, mashed potatoes, milk and the potato water.
Mix well.
Measure flour and RapidRise yeast in bowl.
Add the flour mixture to first mixture.
Knead well.
Allow to rise until double in bulk.
Roll out dough on floured surface, cut doughnuts and place on trays.
Let rise until not quite double.
Fry in hot shortening.
Drain on paper towels. While still hot, these may be dipped in glaze.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Make cake per directions on box.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss rhubarb and sugar together and stir well.
Spoon mixture evenly over cake.
Shake pan from side to side until it settles.
Pour heavy cream over top and shake again until it settles.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 1 hour before serving.
Serve upside down, topped with a dollop of whipped cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: nut balls for tea
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg yolk, orange rind, lemon juice and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour.
Chill.
Using 1/2 tablespoon for each, shape into small balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg white and roll in nuts.
Place a few inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until lightly brown, about 16 to 18 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool with spatula.
Store in tightly covered containers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Skin, stew and cut up chicken.
Melt margarine.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken, soups and Veg-All together.
Pour into pan.
Make holes in mixture with a fork.
Pour melted margarine over top of mixture.
Mix flour and milk together and pour over top of margarine.
(This makes the crust.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salmon with lemon butter
directions: Salmon:
Lay the salmon steaks in a skillet.
Add water and sprinkle with salt.
Heat on medium until water boils.
Lower heat and cover skillet.
Cook the fish 7 minutes.
Lift the cooked salmon from the water.
Place on a warm plate and remove skin. Serve with Lemon-Butter Parsley.

title: "half hour no bake company cake"
directions: Prepare pudding; let set.
Whip cream; fold in crushed pineapple and chill.
Meanwhile, slice chiffon cake so that there are 3 layers.
Spread vanilla pudding mixture between layers and stack them.
Spread whipped cream and pineapple mixture on top and sides sparingly.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: kathy's garlic potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Drain and mash.
Stir in cream cheese, chives and garlic.
Pour into casserole dish.
Pour melted margarine on top; bake until hot.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place the raw stew beef in bottom of 2-quart covered casserole dish.
Layer the onions, celery, carrots and potatoes in order given.
Spread soup over the top.
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook hen and debone.
Put oil in skillet; add pepper, onions, green onions and celery.
Cook until they turn dark.
Add parsley, garlic, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and bay leaf.
Add to chicken.
Boil package of spaghetti in chicken broth.
When done, add to chicken mixture.
Put plenty of liquid in and cook for about 15 minutes on low heat.

title: halvah
directions: Brown flour in a frying pan over low heat, stirring constantly for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
To the flour, add sugar, cinnamon and oil away from heat, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add water and reheat, stirring for 5 minutes until Halvah thickens. Cover and simmer slowly for 5 more minutes.
Fold in walnuts.
Let cool and then cut into squares.

title: raspberry pie
directions: *After fitting the pie crust to the pan, I chill it and then prick it with a fork on the sides and bottom and bake until light brown in a 425° oven.

title: hot texas red chili
directions: With olive oil hot in a large pot, add meat and sear at a high heat, stirring constantly until grey in color (not brown).
Add water and cook at bubbling simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Add all ingredients except flour and corn meal.
Cook additional 30 minutes.
Mix flour and corn meal in 1/2 cup water and add to mixture.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Add water if needed.

title: special k bars
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar to a boil, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Immediately add peanut butter, stirring until smooth. Mix with cereal until cereal is well coated. Spread in a greased 10 x 15 rimmed cookie sheet. Pat down with wet hands. Melt 1 cup chocolate chips and 1 cup butterscotch chips over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and spread over bars. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Render until clear, 1/2 medium chopped onion in olive or vegetable oil.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
When the sauce comes to a boil, drop in the meatballs.
Bring back to a boil, then simmer for about 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to make sure the sauce does not stick.

title: chick's french dressing
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add soup and oil.
Shake and chill.

title: black forest cake
directions: You may use other pie mix instead of cherry.

title: tostada grande
directions: Clean and shred lettuce and refrigerate in plastic bag or crisper.
Combine 1/2 cup green onion, tomato, green chilies, cilantro, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon each:
oregano, cumin and salt. Toss to mix well.
Set aside.
Combine chicken with olives and remaining green onions, oregano, cumin and salt.
Fry tortillas in hot oil; drain.
To serve, arrange tortilla shells on plate, fill with shredded lettuce and top with chicken mixture, tomato salsa, shredded cheese and guacamole and sour cream if desired.

title: mile high icing
directions: Into a large mixing bowl of an electric mixer, place egg whites and syrup.
Start beating on low speed; then increase to high speed.
Add vanilla.
When mixture holds a peak, spread on cake.

title: no bake oatmeal turtle cookies
directions: Bring butter, sugar, evaporated milk and cocoa to a boil in a small, heavy saucepan.
Boil 1 minute, stirring and being careful not to allow mixture to burn.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Work quickly and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: fudgy nut pie
directions: Mix all items together.
Put mixture in unbaked pie shell. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: dutch dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with onion, green pepper and pimento.
Stir egg, sugar and vinegar (after blending together) over boiling water until thickened.
Mix with remaining 4 ingredients.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: pumpkin soup in pumpkin shell
directions: Melt butter and saute onion until soft.
Add spices and broth; bring to a boil.
Add pumpkin and return to boil.
Lower heat and slowly add cream.
Do not boil.
When thoroughly heated, add brandy.
Adjust seasoning.
Pour into pumpkin to serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chops in crock-pot
directions: Brown pork chops slightly on each side.
Put in crock-pot. Put in a can of mushroom soup.
Cook on slow until done.
Serve with rice.

title: never fail zucchini tomato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
You may freeze this after you cook it and warm in microwave.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and bell pepper; saute until tender.
Open all cans and drain everything, then add olives, chopped mushrooms and whole tomatoes (cut the ends off and squash up tomatoes).
Cook for 15 minutes on medium heat.

title: taco twist casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in taco mix and tomato sauce. Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Combine cooked macaroni with 1/2 of cheese and sour cream.
Place in a baking dish.
Top with meat mixture and the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Mix in other ingredients. Using one teaspoon of dough at a time, roll in hand and shape in the form of a crescent moon.
Bake in preheated 325° oven until golden.

title: russian tea cookies(wedding cookie)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt and nuts and stir in.
Chill dough at least 6 hours.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on very lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until set but not brown.
While still warm, roll in sugar.
Cool, roll in sugar again.

title: crab quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble into pieces.
Melt butter; add mushrooms and onions; saute until limp.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Beat eggs and cream together.
Slowly add to cream cheese mixture.
Add crab meat; heat until warm.
Do not boil. Sprinkle bacon and grated cheese on bottom of shell and gently pour liquid into shell.
Set on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: In a 6 to 8-quart saucepan, cook onion and garlic in oil for 5 minutes.
Add parsley, sugar, salt, pepper, tomato paste, tomatoes, water, oregano and bay leaf; stir well.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add meat balls during last half of cooking time.
Stir occasionally.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in large, heavy skillet. Mix in corn, refried beans and remaining ingredients except for tortillas.
Spoon into a greased casserole dish and alternate with layers of tortillas (you might want to cut them up).
Begin and end with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add ground meat and brown.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon mixture into casserole. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: white chili
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and simmer 1 hour. Add chicken. Add Monterey Jack cheese, then add sour cream; let simmer 15 minutes.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole.	 Sprinkle with crumbs.	Bake in 450°
oven
for
15 minutes.

title: ez chili
directions: Heat oil in large pan.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook until onion is just transparent.
Add ground beef.
Brown and drain. Return mixture to heat.
Add tomatoes, Ranch Style beans, garlic powder and chili powder.
Simmer over low heat for 2 hours.
Serve with crackers or warm tortillas.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and top with 1 stack Ritz crackers and 1 stick oleo margarine.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rainbow of peppers
directions: In 3 quart casserole, microwave onion in oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add
tomatoes, sugar, salt, pepper and basil.
Cover and microwave
to
minutes.
Stir
after 3 minutes.
Add peppers and
continue
microwaving
for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand covered for 5 minutes.
Very-very good.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine
oil and sugar.
Add flour (with soda, cinnamon and salt)
alternately with eggs.
Add grated carrots, orange rind and walnuts.
Pour
into
oiled
and floured 9 x 13-inch oblong pan (a loaf or Bundt pan, if you prefer).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or done when tested.
Cool and top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, buttermilk, Wesson oil, hot peppers, shredded cheese, whole kernel corn and diced onion.
Stir and add corn meal.
Pour in large bread pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.

title: microwave spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart microproof casserole.
Cook for 15 minutes on 50, or until very hot.
Remove spices.
Serve hot.
Add red apple slices for garnish, if desired.
Total cooking time: 15 minutes.

title: golden sparklers
directions: For citrus ice cubes, place a thin half-slice of orange, lemon or lime in each compartment of an ice cube tray, with one end of the slice extending above the tray about 3/4-inch. Fill tray with water and freeze for 2 hours or until firm. Pour orange juice and apricot nectar over plain ice cubes in a large (11-cup) glass pitcher or punch bowl. Add sparkling water, stirring gently. Place a citrus ice cube in each punch cup. Pour or ladle juice mixture into cup. Makes 20 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: fudge
directions: Cook to
a rolling boil, then boil 3 minutes.
Put lump of butter
in	when you remove from fire, after cooking.
Cool 10 minutes then beat,	then
add 1 cup chopped marshmallows or nuts; drop from spoon on wax paper.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Microwave on Medium 3 to 5 minutes or until morsels are melted (stir once during cooking).
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes approximately 2 pounds.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Roll chicken in flour. Fry in mixture of olive oil and butter until brown.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle salt, pepper and rosemary.
Pour mixture of wine and broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: plum nectarine vinaigrette
directions: In a heavy saucepan, place plums, nectarines and vinegar. Cook about 10 minutes over medium heat. Cool mixture in refrigerator for about 30 minutes.
Add fruit mixture, honey and seasonings to a food processor fitted with steel blade.
Blend 20 to 30 seconds or until mixture is smooth.
Slowly drizzle in the oil while motor is running.
Process 15 to 20 seconds more.
Whisk in fresh minced mint. Enjoy.
Yields 4 cups.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cool squash.
Cut in half and spoon out seeds.
Mix stuffing, soup and onions (if not real moist add a little water).
Stuff into squash shells and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: savory baked eggs
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine; add crumbs and saute until golden.
Remove crumbs and reserve.
Melt remaining margarine.
Add onions and saute until tender, but not brown.
Arrange onions in 9-inch pie pan; break eggs carefully on top of onions.
Sprinkle with sauteed crumbs.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: bread
directions: In a 1-quart measuring container, put in sugar, shortening and salt.
Fill with water to make 1 quart.
Mix 1 pint of water and yeast.
Add to rest of mixture and let set until it foams.
Add 6 cups flour and let rise.
Add 7 cups flour and knead 3 minutes. Let rise 2 times.
Put in pans and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 loaves.

title: halibut bake
directions: Combine onions, butter, dill weed, salt and pepper in 9-inch baking dish.
Bake onion mixture 10 to
15 minutes in 400° oven until onions are brown.
Season fish with salt and pepper; place on onion mixture.
Top with a few of the onion slices.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes in 400° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place drained beans in bottom of baking dish and layer corn on top.
Mix soup, onions, sour cream, cheese and garlic salt and pour over corn and beans.
Mix margarine, crackers and nuts and pour on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hearty beef turnovers
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, onion and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes; cool.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate. Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain. Stir in seasoning mix. Spread in pie plate; top with chilies.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs, vanilla and sour cream and pour into 11 x 13-inch pan.
In separate bowl, mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over cake and swirl with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple-cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add sugar to juice.
Add jello to water and dissolve, then mix.
When cool, add cream cheese, whipping cream, nuts, cherries and pineapple.
Chill.

title: instant pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients in sealable jar or bowl.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: mandarin orange-sour cream salad
directions: Do not drain fruit. Combine all ingredients. Stir until marshmallows begin to melt. Place in refrigerator overnight. Stir occasionally to mix.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle lemon juice and mix with filling.
Combine dry cake mix and melted butter.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: celery casserole
directions: In sauce pan boil for 5 minutes soup, milk, water chestnuts, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix crackers and butter together to make crumbs.
Place celery in a baking dish, pour soup mixture over celery; and top with cracker mixture.	Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: applesauce cake loaf
directions: Grease and flour pan lightly.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients except the nuts. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes clean at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cook all in pan.
Thaw bread dough.
Cut into pieces and put into greased pans.
Pour hot liquid over dough.
Bake in oven at 350° until done, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not boil mixture.
This makes a double batch.
Use two 9 x 13 pans, greased.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; blend in eggs and stir in dry ingredients, then add peanut butter and flavoring.
Roll into balls about the size of a quarter.
Place on a cookie sheet, ungreased, then flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles and rinse; brown meat, add spices.
Combine noodles, cottage cheese, chopped onions and sour cream. Alternate, layer of noodles and meat.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Spread the dry cake mix over mixture. Mix together the pecans and butter; pour over dry cake mix.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and flip over.

title: dilled meatballs
directions: In large bowl, mix beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon dill weed.
With hands, form mixture into small meatballs.
In skillet in hot oil, cook meatballs a few at a time and brown on all sides.
With slotted spoon, remove meatballs to large bowl as they brown.
When all are cooked, drain off remaining oil from skillet.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water until thick.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Stir hot mixture into egg yolks.
Add remaining mixture.
Cook about 2 minutes longer.
Cool and add vanilla and 1/2 cup coconut. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue and remaining coconut. Bake in oven for 15 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is boiled out.
Mix the dry ingredients; add oil, eggs, nuts, raisins and applesauce. Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: frosted drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla to milk. Cream butter and sugar together for 2 minutes on number 7 speed. Add unbeaten egg yolk and beat 1 minute longer.
Beat egg white 1 1/2 minutes on number 9 until stiff; set aside.
Add flour mixture and milk mixture alternately to the creamed butter and sugar and add.
Begin with flour and end with flour.
Work quickly, but don't overbeat.
Use mixer on number 3 speed.
Fold in egg whites.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients until well blended.
Shape into small balls.
Chill for a few hours; place on waxed paper.
Melt the paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate; chill until firm.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add refried beans, chili beans, Cheddar cheese, soup and taco seasoning.
Cook until hot and well blended.
Put shredded cheese on top.
Let melt, then cool to thicken.

title: burger bean cups
directions: Thoroughly mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Divide into 4 equal parts and place in casserole dish.
Flatten to 5-inch circles.
Turn up edges to form a ring.

title: soft spray for mosquitoes
directions: Mix ingredients in any spray bottle.
Very good to spray animals.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons granulated sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of 10-inch pie/quiche plate.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Chop lettuce and put in bottom of salad bowl. Spread onion over top; spread salad dressing over onion. Sprinkle drained peas on salad dressing, then cheese and add bacon last. Refrigerate. Toss before serving.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and shape into a log. Cover with wax paper and chill. Slice thin. Bake at 350° 8-10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together and place the bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot blueberry sauce
directions: Wash blueberries and drain well.
Mix with the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot over ice cream, waffles, pancakes, pudding or cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice and salt.
Add chicken, rice, pimentos, water chestnuts and onion.
Put into lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Spray rectangular baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange the chicken pieces, skin side up, in the dish. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs.
Blend in oil, vanilla and milk.
Add liquid to dry mixture. Stir quickly just until moistened.
Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into well-greased 2 1/2-inch muffin tins or paper muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stuffed super shells
directions: Put generous layer of spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix eggs, Mozzarella, Ricotta, parsley, salt, ground beef and garlic salt.
Fill shells with mixture.
Place shells in dish over sauce.
Pour remainder of sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma lanham's fried cornbread
directions: Mix until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot griddle or iron skillet, lightly greased.
Brown on one side, then turn over and brown other side.
Serve with butter.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake
mix,	eggs,
oranges and oil well with mixer. Bake in 2
layers or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove meat from the bones.
Place chicken in the bottom of a pan.
Save 1 cup of broth.
Melt margarine.
Put dressing on top of chicken, cream of celery, cream of chicken and sour cream.
Then pour melted margarine and broth over stuffing crumbs.
Place in oven for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put in large casserole.
Add all ingredients, but cabbage.
Bake until tender, 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven; stir in chopped cabbage.
Bake until cabbage is done.

title: tamales
directions: You will need deli paper.

title: easy pizza
directions: Use an 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet or 3 pie pans.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix water, yeast and syrup; wait a few minutes to foam, showing yeast is good.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Let rise a short time (1/4 to 1/3 size).
Roll out to fit pan.
Stretch to make fit; pinch to make edge.
Spread tomato paste around.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic and oregano. Top with cheese slices.
Top with mushrooms, peppers and meat. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon oil.
Bake.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Pour uncooked rice over frozen broccoli and mix well.
In a large saucepan, heat soups and margarine until margarine is melted.
Blend in Cheez Whiz and stir until smooth.
Pour over broccoli mixture and stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: green beans and sesame oil
directions: Cook beans; drain.
Cook other ingredients in saucepan over medium heat.
Keep stirring until golden brown, then pour over beans and serve.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Make a medium white sauce. Melt butter over low heat. Add flour and cook a few minutes, stirring. Add milk and stir constantly until thickened, about 10 minutes. Salt and cook the cabbage with very little water until tender. Drain well. Combine cheese. Grease a large baking dish. Layer all of the cabbage, half of the cheese and all of the white sauce. Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with cornflake crumbs. Bake at 350° until heated through and the cheese is golden brown, about 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: orange marmalade rolls
directions: Pierce, cut off package Pillsbury rolls.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with butter and orange marmalade.
Roll up and wet edges to hold them together.
Slice off and put in muffin pan.
Let rise 2 hours and bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken bombay
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart oblong casserole in 350° oven.
Remove from oven.
Stir in curry powder and ginger.
Place 6 chicken pieces (thick side down) in pan.
Season with salt and pepper. Top with onion, apple and raisins.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and cook, uncovered, until tender.
Remove from pan.
Add rice to sauce in pan.
Put chicken on top of rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: italian beef
directions: Slow cook in crock-pot until tender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease loaf pan with nonfat spray.
Heat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
May add raisins or nuts (1/2 cup), if desired.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Beat all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water and beat until will stand in a stiff peak.
Remove from heat and add vanilla; beat until stiff.

title: french bread barbecue pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice bread lengthwise from end to end. Place both halves on ungreased cookie sheet.
Combine oil and garlic in small bowl and brush on cut side of bread.
In medium saucepan, combine ham, onion and sauce.
Cook on stove for 5 minutes until mixture is hot and onion is tender, stirring frequently.
Spread mixture on bread halves evenly, top with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 generously.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt all ingredients together in saucepan on low heat until desired consistency.

title: tomato bouillon
directions: Cook and strain tomatoes and mangoes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: cabbage rolls or stuffed peppers
directions: Place cabbage leaves in boiling water until wilted good.
Put a spoon of meat mixture in cabbage leaves and roll up.
Place in baking dish.
Pour sauce mixture over them.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
May also be cooked in electric skillet.

title: nice 'n easy fudge!
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in a double boiler.
Heat until melted.
Add nuts.
Pour in a buttered pan.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour, then refrigerate for another hour.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a shallow, 1 1/2 quart baking dish, melt margarine in the oven.
Sprinkle in cracker crumbs; stir well.
Press into bottom of dish to make crust.

title: garden shrimp casserole
directions: Peel the garlic and mince.
Peel the onions and slice thin, then separate into rings.
Cut the green peppers into 1-inch wedges and discard the seeds and stems.
Peel the eggplant and slice 1/4-inch thick, sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Remove ends from the zucchini and slice thin.
Peel the tomatoes and slice thin. Pour 1/4 cup of the oil in a Dutch oven; then add half the garlic and simmer for 1 minute.
Add half the onions and cook for 1 minute longer without browning.
Combine the salt and pepper and sprinkle a small amount over the onions.

Arrange half the green pepper, eggplant, zucchini, shrimp and tomatoes in layers in the Dutch oven, sprinkling each layer with the salt and pepper mixture, then sprinkle with a small amount of the remaining garlic and oil. Repeat the layers, beginning with onions and ending with the shrimp and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with the remaining garlic and oil.
Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to a fast simmer and cover.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Remove the cover and cook for 10 to 20 minutes longer or until the green pepper is tender.
Sauce may be thickened with 2 teaspoons flour, if desired.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour (or Bisquick), then add beaten eggs. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.
Cool before serving.
Pie will make its own crust.

title: christmas punch
directions: I have used different flavors of Kool-Aid and soda, depending on what colors you are working with.

title: pineapple bran muffins
directions: Combine All Bran, applesauce, milk and egg white.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir in pineapple, juice and cinnamon.
Fold in flour, brown sugar, soda and salt.
Spoon into muffin pans (sprayed with Pam or paper lined).
Makes 10 muffins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Dredge raisins with small amount of flour.
Sift together the dry ingredients. Alternate by adding flour and milk.
Add honey and figs.
Fold in raisins and almonds.
Pour into Bundt or tube pan (well-greased). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes a nice holiday cake.

title: jean's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger in butter; add onion, bell pepper, parsley, oregano and garlic powder.
Drain corn and save liquid.
Add corn can of tomato sauce to meat mixture and fry for 10 minutes.
Add water and juice from corn and simmer for a few minutes more. Serve over hot rice.

title: belgian potatoes
directions: Spread layer of potatoes on bottom of round casserole dish (1 1/2 to 2-quarts).
Pour half mixture of soup and milk over potatoes.
Spread onion, pepper and seasonings on top.
Repeat with all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer uncovered to brown the top.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Combine water and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add grits.
Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, 10 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, cheese roll, Worcestershire and garlic powder.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer.
Serve on buns.

title: tangy chili sauce appetizers
directions: Melt jelly on stove, then add both to crock-pot.
Cook on low setting.
Add little sausages or meatballs.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together the first 8 ingredients and stir to blend.
To this mixture, add remaining ingredients.
Beat mixture for 4 minutes, then place in one large or two small greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for one hour, or until done when tested.
(I find it takes a little over an hour, using 2 loaf pans.)
This freezes very well.

title: fresh fruit topping
directions: Mix orange juice, milk, syrup and pudding together until well blended.
Add the Cool Whip.
Chill until ready to serve with fresh fruit.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix with mixer, vanilla pudding and milk until thick.
Add vanilla; blend in Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
In a large bowl, place a layer of crushed vanilla wafers; add a layer of sliced bananas.
Next, pour some of pudding mixture on top. Repeat layers until all is used.
Sprinkle crushed wafers on top. Chill well before serving.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except marshmallows.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan (well-greased).
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes. Immediately after cake is removed from oven, sprinkle with miniature marshmallows.
Cool.
Pour icing over marshmallows.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop cabbage, peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Salt and let stand 3 hours, then press or drain.
Cook in sugar and vinegar for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Then put in refrigerator for one hour.
Then shape into patties, then cover with bread crumbs.
Let chill again.
Then fry until golden brown.

title: lightened spaghetti a la carbonara
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Spray nonstick pan with Pam and cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
In same pan, combine egg, peas, milk and peppers.
Cook for 6 minutes over medium high heat.
Do not boil.
Stir in bacon and half of cheese. Heat through.
Pour over hot noodles and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serves 4.

title: chicken wings pacifica
directions: Disjoint wings, discarding bony tips. Arrange parts in 9x13 inch baking pan (or larger). Combine all ingredients and heat until butter and sugar dissolve. Cool and pour over wings. Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours, turning occasionally. Bake, in marinade, at 350° for 45 minutes, turning once and spooning marinade over chicken occasionally. Drain on paper towels and serve hot or cold.

title: old-fashioned german spice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make little balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar.
Do not pres flat.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar; cream until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, candied fruit and nuts.
Line 2 medium loaf pans with foil; pour in batter.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Store in refrigerator after cool.

title: black walnut cake(indiana picnic cake)
directions: Prepare a 9 x 13-inch pan by lining with wax paper and grease well.
If nonstick, only grease well.
Do not use sprays.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: zucchini squash cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix squash, sugar, oil and eggs. Combine dry ingredients.
Mix with squash mixture.

title: bread pudding that slices
directions: Soak crumbs in 1 cup milk; squeeze dry.
To crumbs, add the remaining cup of milk, beaten eggs, melted butter, sugar, salt, spices and almond extract.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in raisins and almonds.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan or 9-inch tube angel cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Slice and serve warm with whipped cream.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Shape ground beef into 8 patties; sprinkle with garlic powder, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Brown lightly on both sides in oil in skillet; remove to 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Top with onion rings.
Add flour and water to drippings in skillet, stirring to deglaze.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over patties.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes and green peas.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: fancy french toast
directions: Arrange bread in shallow 2-quart baking dish. Beat eggs, milk, Grand Marnier, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Cook in butter on medium-high skillet for 3 to 4 minutes, 2 minutes on other side.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend until smooth all, except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve with assortment of fresh veggies.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour with pineapple juice and sugar.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks, mix well.
Pour into buttered (1-quart) casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and crumbs.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Bubbly and cheese melts.
