title: cream cheese pineapple delight sandwich spread
directions: Add cherry juice, almond flavoring and sugar to cream cheese. Add crushed pineapple, mayonnaise, chopped nuts and cherries; mix well.
Spread on raisin date or white bread.

title: super strawberry shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients, except strawberries, until soft dough forms.
Spread in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes; cut into serving pieces.
Split each piece horizontally.
Fill and top each serving with strawberries.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meat on medium-high in a little oil until brown.
Put vegetables in and continue stir-frying.
Add a few dashes of Worcestershire.
Fry until vegetables are cooked enough.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut up frozen or thawed dough into bite size pieces.
Coat with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan coated with Pam.
Combine margarine, sugars and ice cream.
Boil one minute.
Pour mixture over dough.
Let raise overnight.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins and water and boil 5 minutes.
Blend sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Add to raisins and cook, stirring until clear.
Remove from heat and stir in vinegar and margarine. Cool slightly and turn into pastry lined pan.
Cover with top pastry or lattice strips.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown hash browns in oil.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread potatoes in dish.
Pour eggs over potatoes, top with salt, pepper and bacon bits.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
The next day cook for 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
Remove foil and bake 5 more minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Place 1/4 of bottle of barbecue sauce into baking dish.
Place chicken into dish, cover with barbecue sauce.
Save a little sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and brush additional sauce onto chicken.
Bake an additional 15 minutes or until browned. Serves 4 to 6.

title: amazing chicken and dumplings(makes 4 servings)
directions: Rub flour on both sides of tortillas, using all of flour; cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Bring broth (and seasonings) to rolling boil.
Drop tortillas in broth.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Stir in chicken and milk until heated.
Let stand off heat for 10 minutes, covered.
Each serving = 1 B, 1 1/2 P, 19 optional calories.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli (just a little), drain and put in a greased baking dish.
Beat eggs.
Mix together: eggs, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and mushroom soup.
Take about 1/4 of this mixture and mix with the broccoli.
Put about 3/4 of the mixture on top of the broccoli; crush Cheese Nips or regular crackers.
Add grated cheese and melted butter or margarine.
Put this on top of casserole and cook 30 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix soups together and pour on top of chicken.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package.
Cover the soup mixture with stuffing.
Heat in 350° oven until heated through and soup is bubbly.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; cool.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
This can be placed in long dish to jell and cut in squares and served on lettuce leaves.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Combine soy sauce, wine, sugar, garlic, salad oil and ginger. Marinate chicken in this mixture at least 1 hour or overnight. Chicken may be baked at 325°, or on an outdoor grill.
Baste 2 or 3 times
while cooking.

title: baked pineapple with cheese
directions: Drain pineapple; save 4 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour and stir in the 4 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine margarine and Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Good with ham or chicken.

title: sausage-rice casserole(makes 6 servings. prep time: 10 minutes.)
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage with onion, stirring to crumble sausage; drain grease. Stir in stewed tomatoes and cooked rice. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish; cover with cheese. Bake covered at 350° for 15 minutes, then uncover for 15 more minutes or until cheese is bubbly. Serve with garlic bread or cornbread.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute onions in oil
(large
pan).
Add tomato puree to oil and onions.
Add corn.
Let mixture get hot.
Beat 2 eggs; add milk and corn meal. Stir eggs, milk and corn meal into hot tomato mixture.
Add salt,
sugar
and
olives.
Let
thicken. Add chili powder mixed in water.
Put
in
quart or 2 small containers. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
(Test with knife to see if done.)

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread and pinch rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Combine mayonnaise, cream cheese, dill weed and onion powder.
Spread over cooled crust.
Garnish with vegetables. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate and cut into slices. (Works great with fat free cream cheese and fat free mayonnaise.)

title: cheese crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll in small balls on cookie sheet; cook about 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Line an 8 x 12-inch pan with graham cracker crust.

title: cornmeal waffles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake in a preheated, oiled waffle iron.
Serve hot or cold.
Cool on cake rack.

title: french dressing
directions: Put ingredients into quart jar in order.
Shake well in jar.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk and cream in a double boiler until hot, stirring constantly.
Add butter, salt, pepper and "Meet-E-Tone."
Drop oysters into pot and allow stew to simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir again and serve in deep bowls with a pat of butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled for a large dish.

title: dirt cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of Oreo cookies.
Mix pudding and milk.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour over crumbs.
Pour remaining cookie crumbs over top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: raisin tarts
directions: Cook raisins, sugar, crackers and water until thick like jam. Add lemon juice and margarine.
Make pie crust, roll out and cut in 4-inch circles.
Put filling in and fold over, press edges together.
Prick tops with fork.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Very good.

title: slim soup
directions: Boil together slowly until cooked.
Yields 10 cups, 46 calories per cup.
This is a T.O.P.S. recipe.

title: old fashioned slaw
directions: Dissolved sugar in vinegar.
Beat in milk until mixture thickens.
Add salt if desired.
Chill well.
Pour over shredded cabbage.

title: creamed chicken with vegetables
directions: In skillet, cook onion in Promise until tender.
Stir in soup and milk.
Add chicken; cook until tender.
Stir in vegetables and potatoes; heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Preparation and cook time:
30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in bottom of 8-inch pie shell.
Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, salt and butter.
Pour over pecans.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: bonnie butter layer cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, butter or margarine and vanilla 5 minutes. Alternate flour and milk until well mixed.
Cook at 350° about 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil tea bags and water; add spices.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Add lemon juice, orange juice and sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mark's famous pancakes
directions: Whisk flour, sugar, salt and nutmeg. In another bowl, beat eggs. Whisk in milk and vanilla. Melt butter over medium heat. Whisk into milk mixture. Add wet to dry. Whisk until well blended. Add small amount of oil into preheated iron skillet and fry as usual. Makes 6 to 8.

title: hearty vegetable stew
directions: In Dutch oven, combine tomatoes, water and spaghetti sauce seasoning.
Blend well.
Add potato and onion.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Put uncooked ground beef into a casserole dish and mash down in the bottom.
Pour on top of meat both cans of soup.
Then put Tater Tots on top and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini freezer preserves
directions: Bring to boil zucchini and 1 cup water.
Boil for 6 minutes. Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Add Jello and boil 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour in containers and freeze.
Do not can.

title: lush(pudding dessert)
directions: Mix together and press in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: microwave apples
directions: Peel and slice apples thinly as if making pie.
Put in microwave-safe bowl, uncovered.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
The microwave intensifies the flavor and no sugar or spices are needed.
Good served hot with chicken or pork or just as a delicious snack.
Make enough, there won't be any leftovers!

title: les grives aux olives(thrushes with olives)
directions: Pluck, singe and draw the thrushes.
Put 2 juniper berries, 2 olives and half a pinch of thyme inside each bird.
Lard and truss.
Put the olive oil in a casserole and heat. Saute the thrushes in the oil for 15 minutes.
Season with pepper and very little salt. Add the rest of the olives and heat for 3 minutes. Serve on slices of bread fried in oil.

title: hermits(a christmas cookie)
directions: Cream Crisco, brown sugar and eggs together.
Stir in coffee. Sift flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Stir into mixture.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Chill at least one hour. Place on baking sheet by teaspoons and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix well in a bowl.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with more nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Then at 350° for 25 minutes, knife inserted will come out clean.
Tastes just like pecan pie.

title: candied pecans(microwave)
directions: Put butter in a microwave-safe dish. Melt butter on power 9 for 1 minute. Stir in sugar, cinnamon and cloves. Cook on power 9 for 1 1/2 minutes or until sugar is dissolved. Stir in
nuts until well coated. Cook on power 9 for 3 to 4 minutes. Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: old fashioned cream of tomato soup
directions: Mix tomatoes, chicken broth, butter, sugar, onion and soda. Simmer 1 hour.
Heat cream in double boiler.
Add cream to hot tomato mixture.
Ready to serve.

title: cheese cake puffs
directions: With a mixer, whip together first 4 ingredients.
Put a vanilla wafer in bottom of foil baking cup. Fill 1/2 of each with cheese mixture. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Cover with pie filling and place in refrigerator.

title: 5-hour beef stew
directions: Mix and put in oven, covered, at 250° for 5 hours.

title: apple blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine butter and sugar in large bowl of electric mixer. Beat on low speed until well combined, about 2 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until very creamy.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift flour, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg together onto a sheet of waxed paper.
Sift again.
Add flour mixture into butter mixture. Combine on low speed.
Core apples; don't peel.
Coarsely chop. Fold apples into batter with walnuts and chocolate chips.
Put into pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: chocolate cherry crazy cake
directions: Line greased 9 x 13-inch pan with large marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix. Remove enough batter for 6 small cupcakes.
Pour remaining batter over marshmallows.
Mix dry jello with pie filling and spread over cake batter (do the best you can).
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: mock cherry pie
directions: Chop cranberries and raisins together.
Add sugar, boiling water, flour and vanilla.
Bake in 2 crusts at 375° until brown.

title: pumpkin cider bread
directions: Warm cider, butter, syrup, pumpkin and salt in a large pot until butter melts.
When mixture is lukewarm, add yeast; let rest 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, 2 cups at a time (add the cornmeal) until dough is thick and sticky.
Knead dough, adding extra flour until dough feels firm.
Place dough into a greased bowl.
Let rise 1 hour in a warm place.
Punch down; knead briefly and divide into 3 loaves.
Place loaves in greased pans.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.

title: english muffin sandwich
directions: Take English muffin and warm it up.
Then cut meat in half and place it on the muffin.
Then take the slice of cheese and put it in a bowl; melt it in the microwave for 30 seconds on High.
Then pour it on the muffin.
Then take your lettuce, chop it up and add it in along with the pepper.

title: cream of peanut soup
directions: Puree nuts with 1/2 cup of the broth.
Cook rice until soft and puree with half cup broth.
Combine peanuts and rice mixture and add remainder of broth and sherry.
Season to taste.
Heat and serve.

title: oreo chocolate dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Melt butter and make a crust with cookies and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften 1/2 gallon ice cream.
Put ice cream over crust and freeze 30 to 45 minutes.
Next, boil to a rolling boil a can of Hershey's syrup and sweetened condensed milk. Add 1/2 stick butter.
(It will look like hot fudge.)
Cool. Remove ice cream from freezer and put chocolate syrup over it. Cover with Cool Whip and nuts and put back into freezer until ready to serve.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Bring water to boil; add tea bags and cinnamon sticks.
Steep 10 minutes.
Remove bags and cinnamon sticks.
Add orange juice, lemonade and sugar.
Mix well.
Serve hot.
Keeps in refrigerator. Heat as needed.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Sauce:
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, tomatoes, tomato sauce, soup, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: daddy's soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
In pressure cooker, put potatoes, onion soup mix or onion, lemon pepper, meat and celery.
Cover with water.
Pressure for 15 minutes.
Add spices and canned vegetables. Heat again.
It is ready to serve at this time.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil until creamy.
Add flour, a little at a time; blend well.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour into tube pan; bake at 375° for 1 hour. Remove from pan after about 30 minutes.

title: tomato dumplins
directions: Mix eggs, oil, salt, baking powder and enough flour to make stiff dough.
Roll thin.
Cut in narrow strips.
Add boiling tomatoes.
Add oleo and sugar.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all together and stir over low heat until margarine melts and it thickens.
Cool some, then add 4 or 5 thinly chopped apples.
Mix well and pour into 8 x 9-inch dish.
Top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with chopped nuts and/or cherries, if desired. (Double the recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: strawberry butter
directions: Place all ingredients in container of blender or food processor. Whip until smooth and light.
Delicious as a spread for warm biscuits or beer bread.

title: surprise! surprise! cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour cherry pie filling into mixture.
Beat at 325° until center is done.
Spoon icing onto hot cake.
Broil until bubbly!

title: chocolate crispy bars
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil in a 3-quart pan.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, mixing well.
Add rice cereal. Press mixture into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chips together over hot water.
Spread over cereal mixture in pan. Chill until top is firm.
Cut into bars.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into two 9-inch pie shells. Bake at 350° until firm to touch (30 to 45 minutes).
Makes 2 pies.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Mix strawberries, pineapple and frozen lemonade in a blender. Mix in Kool-Aid; add pineapple juice and water.
Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: sunday night chili
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large pot.
Add the tomatoes, celery, pepper, salt, ground pepper, chili powder, garlic and oregano.
Cover and boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes. Add kidney beans and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: grilled p b and jelly
directions: Make a peanut butter and jelly sandwich. Butter the outside. Grill in frying pan on medium-low heat until lightly brown on both sides. Serve with milk.

title: eclair cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, pudding and milk together for 3 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on top and add another layer of graham crackers.
Spread rest of mixture over crackers and add another layer of crackers.
Top with milk chocolate frosting. (Suggestion:
Soften frosting in microwave for about a minute.) Chill cake for about 4 hours before serving.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until done.

title: crinkle top peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream sugars and margarine until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg, peanut butter and vanilla.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream first 3 ingredients.
Mix in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in next 2 ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Immediately after taking pan out of oven, sprinkle chocolate chips over and let stand 10 minutes; spread evenly. Drizzle on top:

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with a layer of crackers.
Combine butter, sugar, milk and egg.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and add coconut, nuts and cracker crumbs.
Spread over layer of crackers; immediately top with another layer of crackers.
Frost.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 250°
for 35 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix all other ingredients and add to macaroni. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pulled molasses candy
directions: Place molasses, sugar, water and vinegar in saucepan.
Cook until boiling, stirring constantly.
When boiling, add cream of tartar and boil until brittle, 265° on thermometer.
Test in cold water.
Add butter and soda and pour on buttered platter until cool.
When cooled, butter hands and pull until light brown.
Cut with scissors.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix the Veg-All, soup, broth and chicken meat together.
Put into a baking dish. Gradually add the milk to the flour while stirring and then add the margarine.
Pour over the first mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Place each breast half on sheet of wax paper.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using meat mallet or rolling pin.
Place one slice of ham and one slice of Swiss cheese in center of each piece.
Sprinkle evenly with parsley and pepper.
Roll lengthwise and secure with toothpick.
Dip each chicken breast in egg.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Brown chicken to 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan, reserving drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients to drippings and stir.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger cornbread
directions: Brown beef; drain and set aside. Mix corn meal, corn, milk, egg and bacon grease; mix. Pour half in skillet. Pour hamburger over mix. Sprinkle cheese over mix. Pour the rest of batter. Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Combine first two ingredients.
Add next two.
Place in punch bowl.
Break cake into pieces.
Toss lightly.
Mix strawberries and glaze together and pour over cake.
Refrigerate.

title: dill pickles
directions: Mix the vinegar, water and salt together and bring to a hard boil.
Place the next four ingredients in each jar.
Add cucumbers.
Pour liquid mixture into each jar.
Seal jars.
Set jars in hot water and boil for 10 minutes to seal the jars. Gently turn the jars to mix the spices.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and pour into 2 greased and lightly floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pistachio dream
directions: Put pineapple, cherries and pecans in bowl.
Sprinkle pudding over it and mix thoroughly.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: black bottom cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine chocolate crumbs, melted butter and cinnamon in large bowl.
Press into bottom of prepared pan.
Set aside.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Cook rice as directed and spoon into buttered baking dish. Scald milk with butter.
Beat eggs slightly with sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir milk into egg mixture.
Pour over rice. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place baking dish in metal cake pan.
Place on oven rack and carefully pour 1-inch boiling water into cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Good served warm or cold. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pineapple and coconut bread pudding(sugar-free)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: low cholesterol pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes then at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados with a tiny amount of lemon juice, about a tablespoon of mayonnaise and as much hot pepper sauce as you like! Add a little salt.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Pour off excess grease. Place in a large casserole dish. Mix soup and milk together. Pour over hamburger. Place Tater Tots over mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cape cod pasta strudel (lasagna)
directions: Peel sausage and cut up into large saucepan.
Brown sausage and beef together; add onion and garlic.

Stir until well browned. Add sugar, salt, basil, fennel seed, pepper and half of parsley. Mix and add tomatoes, tomato paste (mash up) and 1/2 cup water. Bring to boil and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring a bit.

title: baked french bread toast
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Diagonally cut bread into 1-inch slices and place in pan until full.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, lightly beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in milk until well blended.
Pour mixture over bread in pan, turning slices to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut butter until coarse crumbs are formed.
Turn bread over and scatter blueberries over bread.
Sprinkle top with crumb mixture.
Bake 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and top with strawberries.

title: cheese tortellini savory broth
directions: Boil water and bouillon in stockpot. Stir in pasta; cook for 5 to 6 minutes. Reduce heat to low; stir in zucchini and tomato. Cook until vegetables are heated through. Sprinkle with cheese before serving. Season with ground black pepper.

title: chicken green bean casserole
directions: Grease baking dish and line with crushed potato chips.
Mix soup, milk and salt in bowl.
Fold in chicken, green beans, onions and cheese.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with more potato chips. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Put French fried onions on top.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Put salt over cucumbers and onions and let set 3 hours. Mix sugar,
spices
and
vinegar. Drain cucumbers and onions. Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Bring to boil and can in glass jars.

title: noodle beef stroganoff
directions: In
large
skillet,
melt
butter over medium heat; add beef and brown on all sides.
Stir in onion and cook 1 minute. Add bouillon
cube,
1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper, garlic powder and 1 cup water.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender. Blend
flour and 2 tablespoons water to make a smooth paste; stir into skillet.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Stir in yogurt;
remove from
heat.
While beef is cooking, gradually add noodles
and 1 tablespoon salt to 3 quarts rapidly boiling water.
Cook uncovered,
stirring occasionally, until tender. Drain
in colander.
Serve noodles with beef and sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes
directions: In a greased 1-quart baking dish, layer half the sweet potato slices, apple slices and crumbs. Repeat layers. Pour corn syrup over top and sprinkle with salt. Dot with butter and sprinkle with nuts. Cover and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken siciliana
directions: Place chicken in one layer in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan, skin side down.
Season with salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, mix tomato, seasonings and oil.
With a spoon, spread 1/2 the tomato mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Turn chicken pieces over, salt and pepper and spread on remaining tomato mixture.
Continue baking, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Blend shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, molasses and dry ingredients, except flour; mix well.
Gradually add flour. Roll dough by hand into a small ball about the size of a quarter. Roll dough ball in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; do not flatten!
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix egg, cheese, mayo and soup.
Combine broccoli with mixture and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs or Durkee onions.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer in bowl with lid.
Spread salad dressing over, sealing it against sides of bowl.
Sprinkle sugar over top, then cover. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Put lid on container and let stand for 24 hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: johnnie fines chow chow
directions: Mix tomatoes (if too juicy, drain off some of juice), onions, salt and peppers.
Let stand for 2 hours and drain.
Add sugar, celery seed, dry mustard and vinegar.
Put in jars.

title: earthquake dessert
directions: Grease 10
x 16 x 2-inch cake pan.
Cover bottom of pan with coconut.
Cover coconut with pecans.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Spoon cake mix over coconut and pecans. Combine butter,
powdered
sugar and cream cheese.	Mix until smooth. Spoon over cake mix.
Put small dollops all over cake mix.	Don't try to spread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pina colada ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Follow instructions for your ice cream freezer.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in an 8 x 12-inch pan at 370° for 30 minutes.

title: raw vegetable dish
directions: Dice vegetables rather small.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar substitute and mustard together.
Add diced vegetables to dressing mixture and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: apricot mist
directions: Combine apricot nectar, pineapple juice and limeade concentrate in punch bowl.
Stir in ginger ale.
Add ice cubes. Garnish with lime slices and strawberries or float lime and strawberries on top.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Mix berries and sugar together over medium heat. Bring to a boil. Let boil for 5 minutes.
Add Epsom salts and boil 5 more minutes.
Place in jars and seal good.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Alternately add flour and 7-Up, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab cocktail cakes
directions: In large bowl, blend crabmeat, egg whites, 1/4 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup onions and lemon juice.
Form mixture into 1-inch patties. Combine bread crumbs and dill.
Roll cakes in mixture.
Place on nonstick baking sheet; bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
In small bowl, combine remaining sour cream and onions. Serve cakes garnished with lemon wedges and dipping sour cream mixture.
Makes 16 to 20 (1-inch) appetizers.

title: barbecued beef (or chicken)
directions: Brown beef in a small amount of fat in a skillet.
Transfer meat to a casserole or roaster.

title: mexi-chili casserole
directions: Bake at 375° in 2-quart casserole, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Spread the top with 1 1/2 cups sour cream.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar and corn chips around the edges. Return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: easy make ahead  meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls, about 12 dozen.
Place in single layers on ungreased baking pans.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10- 15 minutes or until no longer pink, turning often.
Drain and cool.
Place about 30 meatballs each into freezer bags. Freeze well for up to 3 months.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add zucchini with basil and stock. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in blender until smooth.
Add cream and season to taste.
Serve hot or cold.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill for a few hours.
Cut into squares and roll in flour. Fry in butter or margarine until brown.
Place in roaster and pour 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 can of water (mixed) over it. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
The soup mixture can be used for the gravy.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Drain pineapple; mash bananas.
Mix jello with water; dissolve.
Add frozen strawberries and juice.
Add pineapple, bananas and nuts.
In mold, allow half mixture to set, about 2 hours.

title: baked huevos rancheros(great for brunch)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with Doritos.
Beat eggs together with milk and add green chiles and onion.
Pour over the chips, then cover this with Monterey Jack cheese.
Cover pan and store overnight in the refrigerator.
Take out next morning and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: easy breakfast squares
directions: Place thawed hash browns in a 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle ham over the hash browns. Top the ham with the two cheeses. Beat eggs. Add milk, salt and onion. Pour over the top of the cheeses. Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 3 hours. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Layer chicken, asparagus, mushrooms, chestnuts and almonds.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan; add onions and cook over medium-low heat until onions are limp but not brown at all. Drain the onions and arrange them in the pastry shell.
Cover with grated cheese.
Beat together eggs, yolks, milk, cream, salt and pepper and pour over the cheese.
Place on lower shelf of the oven and bake at 350° until the pie has puffed in the middle and is golden brown all over (35 to 40 minutes).

title: olive bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Slice bread into halves lengthwise.
Spread mixture on bottom halves of bread.
Replace tops.
Slice bread to, but not through, bottom.
Wrap in foil.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Yield: 20 servings.

title: orange cream
directions: In a large saucepan, combine orange juice, cinnamon sticks and vanilla over medium-high heat.
Bring mixture to a boil and reduce to low heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Stir in ice cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until heated through.
Do not allow mixture to boil.
Serve with miniature marshmallows.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put cheese in microwave until soft. Mix with Bisquick and sausage. (Works best mixing with hands.) Roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extracts.

title: appetizer
directions: Mix well and put in bottom of square bowl.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: streusel cake
directions: Mix with hands the first 5 ingredients.
Mix the cake mix as directed.
Pour half into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble half of the topping over this. Add rest of the batter. Top with remaining topping. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Toss gently to blend.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water and cool.
Add carrots, sour cream, pineapple and walnuts and pour into mold.
Can add cherries for color.

title: meat balls with mushroom soup
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion and salt.
Add enough milk to moisten. Shape into about 32 small meat balls.
Place them on a broiler pan and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove them from the oven and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown on top.
Serve over rice or noodles. (If you'd like more gravy, increase the amount of soup and water.)

title: biscotti
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, until fluffy. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Then stir into butter mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Divide dough into 3 parts. Shape each part into long rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place each roll on an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten top.
The older the cookie sheet, the better I think they come out.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, cut 3/4-inch slices.
Arrange slices, cut side down, on cookie sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake slices another 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: raisin cream bars
directions: Cook
raisins
in
water
until
the water is absorbed. Cream butter
and
sugar;
add oatmeal, soda and flour.
Mix. Put half of	the
batter
in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes
Combine
egg
yolks, sour cream, sugar and cornstarch
and mix
well.	Stir
and
boil until thick.
Add raisins and vanilla.
Pour
over baked crust and add the rest of the crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes longer at 350°.

title: mom's corn fritters
directions: Sift flour.
Mix with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg lightly and add with milk to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon into hot oil in frying pan and brown lightly on both sides.
Serve hot. Makes about 20 fritters.

title: tuna patties
directions: Drain tuna and dump into mixing bowl.
Add chips and stir lightly.
Measure milk and egg into a cup and whip with a fork. Add to tuna mixture.
Add lemon and mix.
Preheat skillet containing oil.
Drop tablespoonfuls of mixture into skillet and smash with a fork or spatula.
Cook until golden brown; turn and cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes several, depending on size dropped.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: summer tomato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let marinate 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: cocoa fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add cocoa and beat 1 minute with spoon or until smooth, stirring constantly.

title: hellmann's magically moist chicken
directions: Brush chicken with mayonnaise. Place bread crumbs in a plastic food bag. Add chicken, one piece at a time; shake to coat well. Arrange on rack in broiler pan. Bake in 425° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all
ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cover with
another pie tin.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 350°
and
bake
minutes.
Makes
3 pies if recipe is doubled.

title: pistachio jello salad
directions: Mix crust ingredients together like pie crust with hands. Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Put lemon juice over mashed bananas.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap and then freeze.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let thaw in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: braised pork chops
directions: Cut a slit in the thickest part of the pork chops to make a pocket.
In a food processor, chop together the rosemary, garlic, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff chops.
In large skillet, heat oil and brown on all sides.
Add mushrooms and saute for 4 minutes, then add water and soy sauce.
Lower heat and cook for 10 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Place cereals, nuts, pretzels and contents of seasoning
pack in large resealable plastic bag; seal bag and shake contents well. Open bag and pour in melted margarine.
Reseal bag and shake until all pieces are coated evenly.
Transfer mix to large microwave-safe bowl; microwave on High for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring every minute.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Makes 4 cups.

title: easy bread and butter pickles
directions: Drain the pickles and slice. Layer the pickles, sugar, pickles, sugar to the top of the jar. Add 3 drops of oil of cloves and 3 drops of cinnamon at the top of the pickles. Put the top back on and let stand for 1 week. It will make its own juice.

title: classic deviled eggs
directions: Cook eggs until hard-boiled. Shell and cut in half and remove yolks. Mix all ingredients together with yolks and stuff eggs.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Lightly grease 10 1/2-inch pie pan.
Cook and drain broccoli. Mix with onion, pepper and cheese.
Put in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients in blender 15 seconds on high.
Pour over vegetables. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Cool 5 minutes and serve.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Stir in chocolate; add egg.
Beat 5 minutes on high speed.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip; pour into chocolate crust.
Chill 2 hours.

title: onion pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large frying pan, heat oil until hot. Saute onions until soft.
In large bowl, whisk together the eggs, cheese and seasonings.
Put onions into unbaked pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over onions; sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake on middle oven rack for 35 to 40 minutes, or until tester comes out clean.
Yields 6 servings.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Add potatoes and onion to boiling water.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Mash potatoes slightly with fork to thicken soup if desired.
Add milk, butter and seasonings.
Heat.

title: crescent sausage rolls
directions: Thaw sausage- Open crescent roll. Unroll and break into 4 rectangular strips. Cover with sausage. Roll up. Use separate knife to cut each roll (easier if you put roll In refrigerator to get cold) I get 5 pinwheels out of each roll=20. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350 degrees. 12 - 15 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with hands.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Kids of all ages love these!

title: oatmeal-apple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
(A good afternoon snack.) Yields 4 dozen.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In medium bowl, beat milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Spread evenly over crust. Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store covered in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in dish; cover with sour cream and chicken soup mixture.
Top with crushed crackers and pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Pour dressing over warm potatoes; chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onions and chopped egg whites.
Add sieved yolks.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and horseradish mustard.
Fold into salad.
Add salt and celery seed to taste.
Chill 2 hours.
Add 1/2 cup diced, pared cucumber if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion and let simmer until onion turns light brown.
Pour all ingredients in casserole dish and cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain excess fat.
Layer meat with tortillas in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add onions and tomatoes.
Combine soup and milk and pour over top.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes on low.
Add cheese after casserole is cooked.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut the broccoli into flowerets.
Cut the tomatoes and onion into diced pieces.
Shred the cheese.
Mix all together.
Add dressing to leave overnight.

title: bacon and cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve on rye bread or crackers.

title: no bake instant chocolate cookie pudding
directions: Beat or whisk instant pudding mix and milk about 2 minutes. Cover and chill for 5 minutes.
Stir together cream cheese, whipped topping, blending well.
Place 1 cup crushed cookies evenly on bottom of large bowl or 9 x 9 dish.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook the chicken with celery and onions until tender.
Put the chicken, soup and sour cream in a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with dressing.
Melt butter in hot water and pour over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in oil over low heat, stirring occasionally, for about 12 to 15 minutes, until tender, but not brown.
Add potatoes and water; cover and cook slowly until tender, about 20 minutes. Force through sieve.
Add seasonings and milk; heat thoroughly. Just before serving, add chopped parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat together first three ingredients.
Add last three ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy cereal bars
directions: Combine morsels and margarine in top of double boiler.
Bring water to boil; reduce heat to low and cook until chocolate melts stirring frequently.
Add marshmallows and cook stirring constantly until marshmallows melt.
Stir in cereals.
Spread mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Let cool.
Cut in bars.
Yield:
20 bars.

title: posole
directions: Wash
and
clean posole; put to boil in large pot.
Add meat, onion, salt and garlic salt.
Boil until tender, about 6 to 7 hours.

title: roger's cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage like for fried cabbage.
Crumble raw hamburger up and put all in 1 cooker.
Add stewed tomatoes, salt, pepper & garlic salt.
Add water & tomato sauce and cook for 30 mins. or until cabbage is tender.
Pour over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, white sugar, salt and margarine together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda; stir well.
Pour over 3 quarts of popped corn and stir well.
Put into flat pan and put in an oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes while baking.

title: vinegar candy
directions: Cook water, sugar, and vinegar over low heat 8-10 minutes or soft ball stage. Add margarine and vanilla. Stir well. Pour onto greased platter until cool enough to handle. With buttered hands, pick up the blob and begin to pull. The more you pull the whiter it gets. Cut into small pieces with scissors. Be sure to keep hands buttered while pulling.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine in a large bowl the oats, whole wheat flour, brown sugar, salt and margarine.
Pour the boiling water over.
Stir into combined ingredients and let set until lukewarm.
Dissolve in a cup the yeast in the warm water and a pinch of sugar.
Stir in the white flour.
Let raise.
Punch down.
Let raise again.
Make out 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mary brogan's jambalaya
directions: Saute chopped onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in the butter.
Add tomatoes, thyme, parsley, chili powder, sugar, salt, pepper, bouillon and wine.
Saute the chicken with sausage.
Add Tabasco to taste.
Add meat and shrimp to veggies.
Saute, stirring, for 1 hour on medium heat.
Serve over rice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lay out on bottom of pan the rolls.
Pour over rolls the sausage that has been cooked and drained.
Sprinkle the hash browns over sausage.
Beat 6 eggs, salt and pepper and 1/2 c milk and pour over hash browns.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onions; add dry ingredients, tomato paste and water.
Simmer 1 hour.
Boil noodles; drain.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: crispix mix
directions: In large bowl, combine cereal mix, pretzels and nuts. Set aside.

In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour seasoning mix over cereal. Gently stir until evenly coated. Pour mixture into 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake at 250° about 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels to cool. Store in airtight container.

title: roti
directions: The night before:
Season meat with onion, curry, seasoned salt, pepper and ginger.

title: ham salad
directions: Run bologna, pickles, eggs and onion through meat grinder. Stir in mayonnaise and season to taste.

title: mincemeat muffins
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix together, then beat at high speed for 3 minutes, scraping sides of bowl as you beat. Pour batter into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Should produce about 24 muffins.

title: oreo cookies
directions: Mix well and bake 7 to 8 minutes for small cookies, longer for large, at 350°, on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Fill with:

title: dr. berd cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients until blended.
Do not use mixer.
Bake in a greased and floured angel food or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Place aluminum foil over cake for last 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute 1/4 cup butter with the onion and celery.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and add flour in large pan.
Add the other ingredients and cook until cheese is melted well.

title: candy bar pizza
directions: Blend oleo, sugars, eggs, vanilla and water; beat until light and fluffy.
Add soda, salt, flour and chips; mix well.
Bake in greased 14-inch pizza pan or a 15 x 10-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let crust cool, then add sauce.

title: crockpot tortilla soup
directions: Cook, debone and shred chicken. Saute garlic and chopped onion in skillet, add to crockpot. Add all ingredients (except toppings) to crockpot, and cook on low for 4 hours, or longer if desired.

title: hamburger-vegetable casserole deluxe
directions: Mix thawed hash browns with the oil, salt and pepper to taste. Spread in bottom and up sides of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish to make a shell.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Prepare meat while potatoes are baking.
Brown hamburger with salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Drain well.
Add gravy mix plus water.
Add package of frozen vegetables.
Steam with meat until vegetables are tender.
Add mushroom soup and 1/2 cup cheese.
Also, add water chestnuts.
Spoon over top of baked potato crust.
Spread other 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Place onion rings over top of all.
Bake 20 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven. Recipe may be doubled.
Use large 11 x 15-inch baking dish.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt butter in pan; add onions.
Saute until tender.
Add crab meat.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli, ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Add ham, broccoli and 1 pack of cheese to macaroni.
In a saucepan mix mustard and oil, heat to gravy consistency.
Put noodle mixture in a casserole dish.
Pour mustard and oil gravy mixture over it.
Then top with other pack of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Cream butter well.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar; cream until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pinch off small pieces of dough.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare rotini to package directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine all ingredients.
Toss before serving.

title: fudge icing
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Add sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Cool to room temperature.
Add flavoring.
Beat until creamy and thick.

title: coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix and pudding. Add water, eggs and oil. Beat at medium speed 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Do not separate rolls.
Cut through the middle, separating the top and bottom of rolls.
Set aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cream sugar and cocoa with eggs and oleo.
Add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate layer pie
directions: Mix flour and margarine together and press into a glass baking dish (7 1/2 x 12). Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of 9 ounce container Cool Whip. Spread on cooled crust.

title: cranberry carrots
directions: Cook carrots according to directions.
Place butter in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart microproof casserole.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) for 1 minute, or until butter is melted.
Add cranberry sauce.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) for 1 minute, or until cranberry sauce is melted.
Stir and mix in cooked carrots. Cook on High (maximum power) for 2 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco well.
Add other ingredients; add milk last!
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Blend well after milk, pouring mixture into floured tube pan.
Bake in cold oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool about 10 minutes, then wrap in foil.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, celery and carrots until tender.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
In a small saucepan, mix chicken and broth. In a shaker, place water and flour and shake well until flour and water is of paste consistency.
Add to boiling broth in saucepan. Turn heat down and stir until it thickens.
Add to vegetables in pie shell and mix well.
Top with second pie shell.
Pierce top crust with knife so steam can release.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs in large bowl. Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls. Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Roll balls into the cinnamon-sugar mixture and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 19 minutes or until set. Remove from cookie sheet. Cool on wire rack. If using self-rising flour, omit cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Crush bananas.
Add eggs, beaten lightly.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes one 5 x 9-inch loaf.

title: pickled okra
directions: Use only small tender okra.
Wash and drain okra, then pack into pint jars.
To each pint add 1 teaspoon dill seed, 1 button garlic and 1 hot pepper.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil. Pour over okra.
Put on lids, screwing bands tight.
Process jars 5 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: stuffed potatoes(serves 4)
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out centers.
Mash together all ingredients, except Parmesan.
Fill shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and a twist of pepper.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 15 minutes, if ingredients are cold.
Has less than one gram of fat per serving.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt and mix well.
Cut in butter until it resembles coarse meal.
Toss apples with water and lemon juice.
Spoon into lightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle flour mixture over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken and broth in 2 quart sauce pan.
Bring to boil. Cut flour tortillas in one inch squares and add to chicken mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 3-4.

title: double green casserole
directions: Cook vegetables together and drain; set aside.	Melt cheese in soup.
Pour 1/2 vegetables into greased 9 x 6-inch baking dish. Cover with cheese mixture.	Repeat.
Crush crackers and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: snack club crackers
directions: Spray cookie sheet generously with Pam.
Lay crackers flat and close together.
Cover cookie sheet with crackers.
Boil butter and sugar for 2 minutes (no more, no less).
Pour over crackers. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan and break apart.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Put cake batter into 3 greased and floured cake pans and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine
sweet potatoes with other ingredients and pour into 9-inch
pie
shell.
Bake
at
425° for 15 minutes.
Turn heat to 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: tuna tetrazzini(yields 6 servings)
directions: Cook onion in small amount of hot fat until tender, not brown. Add soup, milk and cheese.
Heat and stir.
Break tuna fish in chunks; add with remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake in moderate 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with ripe olives.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Beat or process cream cheese, sugar, 1 egg and vanilla.
Spread in bottom of unbaked crust.
Beat or process the rest and pour over first layer.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter; then add rice, soup and oregano.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
Add water occasionally.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Put first 2 ingredients into microwave-safe dish.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir thoroughly and add vanilla.
Pour into foil-lined 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots in salted water.
While carrots cook, cook tomato soup, vinegar, sugar, oil, mustard and worcestershire sauce into syrup, about 15 minutes.
Add green peppers and onion.
Cook another 2 minutes.
Drain carrots.
When tender, pour hot syrup over drained hot carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican rice
directions: Dilute broth as directed on label; set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add rice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until golden brown.
Pour broth in and add chicken, tomato, garlic, peppers and cumin.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: lemonade jello
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add frozen lemonade and mix.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours until slightly set.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Put into jello mold or cups and refrigerate until set.

title: peanut chocolate clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler with Eagle Brand milk. Add peanuts.
Stir and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: very light yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and 1/2 cup warm (not hot) water.
Set aside to dissolve about 5 minutes.
Then mix the sugar, salt, powdered milk and 1 1/2 cups water.
Heat at low on top of stove to dissolve sugar and salt, about 5 minutes.
Allow to get warm boiling hot then add margarine to milk mixture.
(Allow the margarine to melt in milk mixture.)
In a large bowl add 4 cups flour, yeast and milk mixture; then add slightly beaten egg.
Mix well, it will feel elastic.
Then add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Cover bowl and keep in warm area.
Allow dough to double in size, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Then knead dough on well floured area.
Divide into 3 equal parts.
Roll out about 1/2-inch thick and cut rolls with cutter or roll in a small ball and spray baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Cover and let rise until double in size; then, in a hot 400° oven, bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and brush with butter immediately.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix together cookie crumbs and butter.
Pat 2/3 of crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Keep 1/3 crumbs for top.
Beat together the pudding and milk until very thick.
Add the softened ice cream and beat together until well blended.
Pour pudding mixture over the crumbs.
Spread Cool Whip over the pudding mixture and top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 20.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Bake in cast-iron skillet. Spray skillet generously with Pam cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: monkey bread(great for breakfast!)
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
In plastic bag, mix 2/3 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Shake pieces of biscuits in bag and layer in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and mixture of margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Do another layer of biscuits and top with nuts and margarine mixture.
Another layer of biscuits and nuts and margarine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: chicken parmesan and fettucini
directions: Fettucini:
Melt cream and Parmesan cheese over medium heat. Slowly add butter.
Be careful not to scorch cheese and cream. Continue stirring and reduce heat when blended together.
Add parsley and pepper to taste.
Toss together with prepared fettucini.

title: angel food pudding dessert
directions: Tear up cake in pan; mix pudding through it. Spread Cool Whip over the top. Cool and enjoy.

title: kiffels
directions: Let butter and cream cheese sit out until room temperature. Then cream together cheese and butter; add flour.
Roll into one big ball.
Pinch off into small balls, about 50.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine in a pint jar:
ketchup, water, sugar, mustard, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to ground beef.

title: freezer corn relish
directions: Cut corn off the cobs.
Combine all ingredients in a large, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Cool and ladle into pint size Ziploc bags.
Seal and freeze.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir occasionally while cooking.

title: heath bar torte
directions: Make cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool cake 15 to 20 minutes.
Use end of a beater or spoon and poke holes all over cake.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake. Then pour butterscotch caramel over that.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Chill and serve.
A definite crowd pleaser!
Very rich!!

title: wilted spinach mandarin
directions: Separate spinach into leaves.
Swish in cold water.
Repeat several times with fresh cold water to remove sand and grit.
Pat dry with paper towels.
To remove stems from spinach leaves, fold each leaf in half.
Pull stem toward top of leaf; discard stem. Blot any moisture from leaves with paper towels.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli and onion.
Fry bacon crisp and cut up into small pieces.
Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli, onion and bacon and mix.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix eggs, milk, rice, sugar, raisins, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Bake in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 25 minutes.
Stir and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Continue baking approximately 20 to 25 minutes longer until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled with light cream.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thaw shell 20 minutes.
In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onions.
Saute 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and milk.
Stir into onions.
Add chicken and peas.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Add next three ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole for 9-inch or 9 5/8-inch shell.
Remove shell from tin.
Place on top of casserole.
Trim edge if necessary.
Cut slits on top.
Brush with egg.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until golden.

title: catarina thomas' apple pie
directions: Squeeze the juice of the lemon over apple slices.
Mix together sugar, spices and apple slices.
Fill pie shell with this mixture and dot with 1/2 stick butter.
Pour half of the dry cake mix over apples.
Melt 1 stick of butter and pour over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Put pie filling on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan; spread evenly.
Mix together dry cake mix, coconut and nuts.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Drizzle melted butter over this.
Bake at 375°, or 350° for glass dish, for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine salmon, salt, parsley, cayenne pepper and lemon juice. Place cream into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Blend flour and butter; then stir into boiling cream.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Stir salmon mix in and season to taste.
Mix well.
Let cool.
Form into croquettes; roll first in beaten egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Place cut side down in a microwave-safe 2-quart square baking dish.
Microcook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 2 to 3 minutes or until nearly tender (or cook in boiling water for 3 to 4 minutes).
Scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch thick shell.
Set shells aside.
Finely chop the zucchini pulp; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, cook onion in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Add chopped zucchini.
Cook 1 minute more.
Stir in flour, basil and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Gradually add zucchini mixture to the egg product or egg.
Stir in Parmesan; spoon mixture into zucchini shells.
Place in a 2-quart square baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until filling is lightly browned.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Place a scoop of ice cream between two bread slices.
Form around the ice cream and pinch edges together.
Wrap in foil and return to freezer immediately, for at least 2 hours.
Heat oil to almost smoking.
Drop each ice cream bread ball into hot oil individually.
Cook for no more than 10 to 15 seconds per side. Remove.
Garnish with chocolate syrup and whipped topping.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Melt butter; add cracker crumbs.
Place shrimp in buttered baking dish; cover shrimp well with buttered crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Blend first three ingredients.
Chill.
Using 1/2 teaspoon mixture for each, roll into 24 rolls.
Place in 1 1/2-inch paper bonbon cups.
Melt coating and remaining peanut butter, following microwave instructions.
Spoon into cups.
Chill.
Makes 2 dozen. (Extra coating is good with walnuts and marshmallows.)

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, milk, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: shoe peg corn lesueur pea salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Bring to boil sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix and refrigerate.
Stir before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and shortening together.
Beat egg really well.
Add vinegar and water to egg.
Mix well and then add flour mixture.
Put in refrigerator for 1/2 hour before using. Makes 4 balls.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Cut nuts and fruit in three pieces each.
Mix all ingredients together and press in desired dish.

title: soft ginger cake(gingerbread)
directions: Soften butter; beat in sugar.
Add molasses; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients into flour.
Reserve enough flour to coat raisins and currants.

title: dinner cheese biscuits
directions: Place flour in bowl. Cut in margarine with pastry blender until crumbly.
Add buttermilk and mix well. Stir in cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon onto baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes. May bake partially and freeze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take soup, onions, pepper and broth and mix together.
Spoon over chicken cubes.
Top with stuffing mix and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix together flour, buttermilk and mayonnaise.
Spoon into buttered muffin pans.

title: island style chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
In skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add reserved liquid from pineapple, broth, vinegar, sugar, tamari and garlic.
Cover and cook over low heat 40 minutes.
Add pepper and pineapple.
Cook 5 minutes more or until done, stirring occasionally.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Gradually stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Serve with rice.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sift biscuit mix on kneading board and put dough on that and sift more biscuit mix on top of dough.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (approximately 20 minutes).
Brush with butter and serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with nonstick cooking spray. Roll cookie dough onto pizza pan and bake as directed on package. Allow dough/crust to cool.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine enough pineapple juice with sugar and flour to make a paste.
Add pineapple chunks.
Put in buttered dish.
Mix margarine and crackers together and put on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown on top. Delicious!!!

title: coconut butter balls
directions: Cream butter; add sifted sugar and vanilla, then blend in flour and coconut.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm and again after cooled.

title: strawberry punch(serves 20)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze in deep cake pans.
When serving, scoop into punch bowl (no ice necessary).
Enjoy!

title: sugarless christmas pie
directions: Combine eggs, applesauce, milk, liquid sweetener, lemon juice and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 400° until knife comes out clean.

title: steak and potatoes
directions: Sprinkle steak with meat tenderizer and let sit 1 hour.
Cut steak into single portion pieces and dredge each in flour.
Brown on both sides in oil.
Season meat with seasoned salt and pepper as it cooks.
Remove meat and drain on paper towel.
Put soups and milk into frying pan and mix with crusties from meat.
Stir well. Grease a 3-quart casserole and layer meat, potatoes and gravy, ending with gravy.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour with cocoa, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the margarine, oil and sugar.
Stir in vanilla extract, eggs and milk.
Blend well. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix until batter is smooth.
Add zucchini to mixture.
Spread batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased on the bottom and then dusted with cocoa.

Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped nutmeats over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done; edges will begin to leaves sides of pan and top will spring back when lightly touched with finger. Cool in pan on wire rack. Serve cake slightly warm or completely cooled, plain or with ice cream, whipped cream or whipped topping. Serves 15.

title: emma's chicken
directions: Cook chicken and dice.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch squares.
Mix liquids, onion and SALA together.
Butter a large, shallow baking dish.
Add juice to bottom of dish, then a layer of tortillas and a layer of chicken.
Make 2 or 3 layers, ending with the liquid on top.
Cover with cheese and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator. Bake at 300 degrees for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mother's sugared popcorn
directions: Boil together until thread forms.
Remove and add food coloring (few drops of red).
Pour over a large kettle of popped corn; mix well.
Store in a cool place.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir together eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
If desired, serve with whipped cream.

title: 7-up applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot applesauce.
Add cold 7-Up, blending gently.
Chill 2 hours.
Add celery, olives, nuts and lemon juice. Chill 2 hours.
This is good with ham.

title: tropical juice
directions: Combine juices.
Top with sliced orange and a cherry with a toothpick through them.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt the oleo in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over oleo.
In layers, alternate chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and coconut.
Drizzle can of Eagle Brand milk. Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° (chips should be melted).
Let cool and cut.

title: conch fritters
directions: Grind conch fine.
Chop up pepper, tomato and onion.
Beat eggs well.
Mix these ingredients, adding salt, black pepper and flour. Form into fritters; roll in cracker meal and fry in hot shortening until a delicate brown.
Serve with French fries, lime wedges and hot sauce.
Tomato catsup is a favored condiment for this dish also.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream oleo, brown sugar and sugar.
Blend
in egg.
Add 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and
vanilla.
Stir in flour and oatmeal.
Spread in a 10 x 10-inch pan.
Bake
at 350° for 25 minutes.
After baked, top with both kinds
of
chips.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix brown sugar, peanut
butter
and
milk. Spread on top.
Take a spoon and do all around.

title: mound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add the cocoa, mixed with the 3 tablespoons warm water. Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with the buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in three 9-inch prepared round cake pans in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: curried crab in endive spears
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix in crabmeat with pepper to taste.
(Can be prepared 8 hours in advance.) Place 1 heaping teaspoonful of mixture on base of each endive spear.
Sprinkle with cilantro.
Makes 24.

title: onion sandwiches
directions: Soak onion in milk overnight and rinse.
Then, next day, toast like you would toasted cheese sandwiches.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Then debone.
Take Pyrex dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch), mix the rest of the ingredients and add chicken.
Use the broth from the chicken for the water.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until it is brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Let bread thaw in refrigerator overnight.
Butter bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Cut bread into small pieces and place in pan over nuts.
Put pudding, butter, sugar and milk in pan and warm until all is dissolved.
Pour over bread pieces and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out onto plate.

title: french toast
directions: Break eggs into a shallow dish.
Beat eggs slightly with fork. Add milk and salt.
Then mix.
Melt butter on griddle.
Dip bread each side quickly into milk-egg mixture so it is coated but not soaked with mixture.
Put bread on hot griddle and cook over low heat until it is golden brown on side.
Turn and brown other side.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Pound flour into meat; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Alternate layers of steak, onion slices and carrots in a casserole dish.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with steak.
Cover with boiling water.
Cover casserole dish and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Add water as necessary.
Remove cover and brown if needed.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: steak or what?
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Pat ground beef over bottom of pan, then spread potatoes over beef.
Add onion, then the vegetables.
Mix soups together and our over vegetables.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for one hour or until done.
Very good!

title: cucumber and meat slices
directions: Peel cucumber.
Cut into very thin slices.
Cut meat into paper thin slices about 2 inches square.
Add soy sauce, sherry, ginger, sugar, salt and pepper to meat; mix well.
Heat the oil and fry the meat for 2 minutes.
Add cucumber slices and cook over hot heat for 1 minute; stirring all the time.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin and beat well.
Add other ingredients; blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch deep dish pastry shell that has been chilled.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: crab louis
directions: Arrange lettuce on 4 plates.
Put mound of crab meat in center of each. Arrange overlapping slices of eggs, tomatoes and cucumber to form a border.
Serve with mayonnaise.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, beat in eggs. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk. Mix well. Stir in grated lemon rind and nuts. Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3 glass loaf dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool 15 minutes in dish. Remove to wire rack. Pierce top of bread while still warm and pour glaze over top.

title: enchiladas
directions: Put butter on the tortillas, then sprinkle with chili powder. Prepare half the cheese and butter, then put it in the tortilla. Put tortillas in pan.
Mix cheese with grated cheese and sprinkle on top.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Dice in chunks.
Saute onion in margarine with bell pepper.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of chicken soup.
In a casserole dish, put a layer of chips, cheese, then sauteed mixture and chicken.
Repeat again.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: harvest soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain well. Add the water, potatoes, squash, bouillon, bay leaves, chili powder, pepper, allspice and cloves. Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add the tomatoes. Cook and stir until heated thoroughly. Discard bay leaves. Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown the amount of hamburg needed for your size family.
Add a package of Lipton onion soup mix and water or beef broth to make gravy.
Add diced onions, carrots and potatoes.
Cook until veggies are done.
Thicken with cornstarch or flour as you would for gravy.
Serve on baking powder biscuits or mashed potato.

title: fettucini with sausage, red pepper and mushrooms
directions: Remove casing from the sausage; break into very small pieces. In large skillet, cook sausage 5 to 7 minutes or until brown. Remove sausage from pan; drain.
Heat olive oil in skillet; add onion.
Cook until translucent.
Lower heat; add red peppers, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes or until peppers and mushrooms are tender.
Add sausage to this mixture and cook together on low heat 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: crab spread
directions: Blend softened cream cheese.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over the cream cheese.
Pull the mock crab legs in small pieces and add to cheese mixture.
Cut up diced purple onion into cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Make into a ball.
Pour cocktail sauce over the ball when ready to serve.

title: mom's red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Add alternately buttermilk with sifted flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to vinegar.
(Hold over bowl it will foam.)
Add the soda and vinegar, blending instead of beating.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in greased and floured pan.
Cool.
Split each layer into 2 layers and frost and add each layer back on top of each other after frosted.

title: piquant chicken
directions: Combine wine, soy sauce, oil, water, garlic, ginger, oregano and brown sugar in order.
Arrange breasts in a large, greased casserole.
Pour sauce over them.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash and dry grapes.
Put in bowl and set aside.
Soften cream cheese.
Add Miracle Whip and minced garlic.
Mix well.
Pour over grapes and mix.
Chill and serve.

title: tuna cheese pie
directions: Mix milk and salad dressing. Add eggs, cheese, onion, and tuna. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: zesty smoked sausages
directions: Stir together soup, marmalade, vinegar and mustard in a 2-quart
microwave	bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in sausages.
Cover with vented
plastic
wrap and cook at High 7 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Stir halfway through cooking.	Makes about 30 appetizers.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Add enough broth to mushroom liquid to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Cook rice by package directions.
Melt butter and saute onion until tender.
Remove onion and stir flour into butter.
Add mushroom liquid and broth.
Stir until smooth.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach very well.
Combine all ingredients and roll into balls using 1 teaspoon mixture for each.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet. Drain at once on paper towels.
Yields 75 balls.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat by hand until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apricot-lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add oil and apricot nectar; mix with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door while cake is cooking. Glaze.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cottage cheese onto cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients together, adding ripe olives for color.
Serve with chips.

title: lemon-sour cream pie
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Whisk in milk until smooth, then egg yolks until well blended.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Add butter.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thick; do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in sour cream until well blended.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and egg.
Cook in double boiler.
Add lemon juice and grated lemon peel, when thickening begins.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mash and stir cheese until softened.
Blend in salad dressing until smooth.
