Add fruits and cream which has been whipped stiff with the sugar.
Add enough cherry juice to give color, then spoon into molds and freeze firm.
Cover tops with wax paper before freezing.

title: sally's peanut butter pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Add 1 egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add 2nd egg and beat 5 minutes more.
Pour into pie shell and top with chopped, salted peanuts. (Looks good with chocolate shavings, too!)
Serve with whipped cream and/or hot fudge sauce.
Serves 8.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Always	make
the
meringue
with
powdered
sugar
not regular white sugar and, this is the "never fail" part:
add a couple of tablespoonfuls
of marshmallow cream to the mixture. It doesn't
affect
the
taste
at
all but guarantees a high fluffy meringue that doesn't fall or weep.

title: marinated grilled steaks
directions: 24 hours before grilling, mix salad dressing and Worcestershire sauce together in a plastic bag.
Salt steaks with garlic salt and place into the bag.
Make sure all steaks are thoroughly covered with liquid mixture.
Compress bag to remove all air and tie the bag closed.
Refrigerate until time to grill. Grill and enjoy!

title: crock-pot beans(texas beans)
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon separately.
Mix all remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Add meats.
Cook 4 hours on low in crock-pot or 1 hour at 350° in oven.

title: betty ann's chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease shallow 2-quart baking dish. Mix together chicken and vegetables; place in dish.
Stir together chicken broth, soup and pepper; pour over chicken mixture.

title: pickled pears
directions: Place all spices in a cloth bag or nylon net.
Combine water, sugar, spices and vinegar in a pot and cook for 10 minutes.
Add pears and 1/2 bottle of food coloring (red or green).
Cook until pears are tender.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Make the crust by combining the graham cracker crumbs with the melted butter and 1 Tbsp. sugar in a medium bowl.
Stir well enough to coat all of the crumbs with the butter, but not so much as to turn the mixture into paste. Keep it crumbly.
Press the crumbs onto the bottom and about 2/3 of the way up the sides of the springform pan.
You don't want the crust to form all of the way up the back of each slice of cheesecake.
Bake the crust for 5 minutes, then set it aside until you are ready to fill it.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, 1 c. sugar, and vanilla.
Mix with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add the pumpkin, eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg, and allspice and continue to beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour the filling into the pan.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.
The top will turn a bit darker at this point.
Remove from the oven and allow the cheesecake to cool.
When the cheesecake has come to room temperature, put it into the refrigerator.
When the cheesecake has chilled, remove the pan sides and cut the cake into 8 equal pieces.
Serve with a generous portion of whipped cream on top. Serves 8.

title: omelets
directions: In a nonstick skillet, or lightly sprayed skillet with Pam, over medium heat, pour 1/2 cup Second Nature egg mix.
Cook, lifting edges to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath.
When almost set, spoon 1/4 cup sauce over half of the omelet.
With spatula, fold other half over the filling.
Slice onto serving dish and keep warm.
Repeat to make more omelets.
To serve, top each with 1/4 cup sauce.

title: tommy's chicken pot pie
directions: Cover chicken, onion, celery, salt and pepper with water and cook until done; cool.
Cut up chicken in small pieces and add the two diced hard-boiled eggs.
Combine broth from chicken and cream of chicken soup.
Heat, thicken and strain.
Pour over chicken and mix well.
Pour into individual dishes or casserole dish.
Using Bisquick mix, make biscuit recipe and roll thin.
Place on top of chicken mix.
Brush with melted butter and dash of paprika.
Bake until mixture is hot and bubbly, about 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: You'll need a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish, greased and floured.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Use blender if available.
Beat eggs for 1 minute.
Add milk and beat for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and mix for 2 minutes.
Have frying pan coated lightly with butter and pour about 1/4 cup batter into hot pan.
Tilt pan all around so the batter covers the bottom.
These are very thin pancakes; they will appear like a crepe.

title: punczki (raised doughnuts)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add 2 cups flour.
Mix and let stand in warm place 1/2 hour.
Then beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt until light.
Add this to the yeast sponge.
Melt butter. Add to sponge.
Add 5 cups flour.
Mix well until hands are clean. Cover and allow dough to raise 1 hour.
Turn on floured board and pat with hands until dough is 1/2-inch high.
Cut with doughnut cutter, cover and let rise again.
Then fry in hot oil.
Use your favorite icing.

title: mexicali pork chops(microwave)
directions: Trim separable fat from pork chops; sprinkle with salt. In an 8
x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange chops with meatiest portions facing
the
outside
of the dish.
Cover with vented microwave-safe plastic
wrap.
Cook
on
power (medium to low) for
minutes. Turn chops over.
Rotate dish, one-half turn; cook for 10 to 12 minutes more or until chops are tender and no pink
remains.
Transfer
to a serving platter and keep warm.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, apple juice and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir.
Reduce heat to a simmer.
Cover pan; cook, stirring every five minutes, until rice is tender.
Remove from stove. Stir in raisins and cinnamon.

title: vinegar slaw
directions: Add salt to shredded cabbage, carrot and mano; let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Make a syrup.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Cut avocados in half.
Remove seed and scoop out avocado with spoon.
Smash avocado with spoon until some of lumps are gone. Mix onion, tomato, cilantro and salt.
Serve with chips.

title: tropical dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread the cherry filling on bottom. Spread undrained pineapple on top of that, then dump on the dry cake mix. Do not mix the ingredients. Pour the butter evenly over the batter. Spread coconut on the top, then sprinkle on the pecans. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening in flour and salt. Combine milk and vinegar; add to flour and mix, stirring until dough thickens. Makes 2 crusts.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in a roasting pan.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Sprinkle rest of seasoning over top of the meat.
Roast until medium rare, about 2 1/2 hours or internal temperature is 150°.
Slice and serve on hard rolls.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage, scrambled up. Then, add cheese and tomatoes. Cook just enough to heat up cheese and tomatoes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Pour olive oil over while hot; add vinegar, spices and marinate overnight, turning every few hours. Next day, add remaining ingredients.
Good if served with bran muffins.

title: dilly bread
directions: Fix yeast, first, by combining it in a bowl with the 1/4 cup of warm water.
Soak for 5 minutes.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl, adding the yeast and flour to make a stiff dough.
Work well; cover.
Let rise until double in size, 30 to 60 minutes. Work down; put in a greased 8-inch loaf pan.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Butter the top with soft butter.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: chess pie
directions: Heat 1 cup sugar, brown sugar, milk, flour and butter until dissolved.
Let cool.
Beat 1 whole egg, 3 egg yolks and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add to cooled mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn oven down to 250° until firm on edge, about 10 minutes.

title: no bake oat cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and cook for 2 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spoon on wax paper (cookie size) and let cool.
Ready to eat.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Make the Jell-O with boiling water and cool.
Add Cool Whip. Add pineapple (well drained).
Add cottage cheese and mix.
Put cherries on top.

title: german sauerbraten
directions: *If a larger portion of meat is used (and I recommend it), add more water and vinegar, using the same proportion of 3:2.

title: pork chop abracadabra
directions: Brown 4 to 8 pork chops well and season lightly with salt and pepper.
Place in crock-pot and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla, salt and flour.
Roll in small balls and flatten with fork.
Place a nut or cherry on top.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: kathy's "famous" baked pineapple
directions: Pour pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in eggs, flour and sugar.
Break bread into bite size pieces.
Dip them into melted butter.
Place on top of pineapple mixture until covered. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until edges of bread have browned.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in skillet until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes or until hot.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: deep dish strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and jello.
Cook over medium-high heat until thick and transparent.
Cool.
Put berries into a baked and cooled deep dish pie crust and pour jello mixture over berries.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: lemon delight salad
directions: Work like pie crust.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Press into 9x13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off oranges and pineapple.
Add strawberries and peach pie filling; mix well.
Blend in bananas and grapes.
Let set in refrigerator; chill before serving.
This will keep without the fruit turning dark.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat
the cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lemon squares
directions: Beat cake mix, oleo and 1 egg together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture. Chill dough.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
With floured cookie cutters, cut into desired shapes. Using spatula, transfer to baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes in 400° oven.
Decorate, if desired.

title: german matilda applesauce meat loaf
directions: Mix and knead together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 2 hours in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: gone broke chili
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Add all ingredients to drained kidney beans.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes after bringing it to a slow boil, stir occasionally.
Serves many!
You may freeze servings of your choice.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on the box.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, add tomatoes, chili peppers, salt and pepper and simmer about 15 minutes.
Blend sour cream and cream cheese into mixture.
To serve, keep warm over hot water or crock-pot on low.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Then beat in sugar, oil and vanilla until thick. Stir in zucchini and flour (sifted with cinnamon, salt, baking powder and baking soda).
Fold in walnuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 standard loaf pans.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Chop fruit and nuts fine.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Pour 1/2 of dry cake mix over this and mix well.
Mix rest of cake mix, using 1/2 of eggs, oil and water as directed on cake mix.
Pour over fruit mixture and mix well.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake around 12 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini and tomato bake
directions: Place zucchini in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 each of soy sauce, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Layer tomatoes and onion over zucchini; sprinkle with remaining seasoning.
Top with cheese; dot with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan toffee bars
directions: Mix until light and crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Lay pecans on top.
Put 3/4 cup butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar in saucepan.
Boil 50 seconds, stirring constantly.
Pour over mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: best ever pickles
directions: Soak vegetables in salt water for about 3 1/2 hours.
Mix spices and sugar in vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables. Bring to a boil again.
Put in jars to seal.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add taco sauce, both soups (do not add water) and chopped green chilies.
Put half of mixture in casserole dish; layer with Doritos and then cheese.
Layer again with rest of mixture then Doritos and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: "no bake" cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: one pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla, margarine and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into uncooked deep pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in 1 3/4 cups water for 5 minutes. Add sugar and cook 15 minutes. Add nuts after cranberries are cooked.
Add the jello and 3/4 cup cold water. Stir until dissolved and let cool. Add rest of ingredients.

title: refrigerated slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onion together.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour boiling liquid over cabbage mixture.
Cover and let stand 3 hours.
Refrigerate.
Will keep up to 5 to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: turkey stroganoff
directions: Brown turkey in butter.
Stir in flour, soup, consomme, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add mushrooms and sour cream.
Heat until warm.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: holiday green beans
directions: Saut onion in butter.
Add flour, then milk; cook and stir until smooth.
Stir in cheese, Tabasco, soy sauce, pepper and salt.
Cook until cheese melts (stirring frequently to prevent scorching).
Add beans, mushrooms, sliced water chestnuts and pimentos.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins.
Cool and peel; shred coarsely.
Mix melted margarine with cheese and add to potatoes.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in sour cream.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls. Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown meatballs.
Remove from skillet and pour off fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring constantly until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until thoroughly coated.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately or transfer to a slow cooker; keep warm on LOW.

title: marinade for shish-kabobs
directions: Add all ingredients; marinate 2 to 3 hours, not refrigerated.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Grill or cut into bite size pieces and broil. Great served as an appetizer or over rice as a meal.

title: butter pecan banana pudding
directions: Follow directions on box of pudding (mix with pecans).
Layer vanilla wafers on bottom of bowl.

Layer pudding on top of wafers. Layer sliced bananas on pudding. Continue layering wafers, pudding and bananas. Will fill one large bowl and a medium bowl. After all layers are finished, put Cool Whip on top. Garnish with finely crushed pecans.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and
spread on ham slices and roll up.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces. Serve with toothpicks.
Can be made 1 to 2 days ahead and refrigerated.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred cheese.
Let set to room temperature.
Mix ingredients. Form into ball.
Roll in pecan dust.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet; brown.
Drain well and set aside. Line bottom of buttered, 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with the crescent roll dough, firmly pressing perforations to seal. Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over sausage.

title: barb's chopped apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten eggs and mix.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Stir apples into flour mixture.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 35 minutes at 325° or until it passes the toothpick test.
Times vary due to amount of juice in apples. Serve with ice cream and sauce.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place one crust in casserole dish (the crust will need to be floured according to directions on box).
Mix other ingredients and pour in dish over crust.
Place remaining crust over top. Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken to which salt and pepper is added, until well done.
Let cool and remove meat from bones.
Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Add chicken stock and eggs and mix well.
Flour board and knead until smooth.
Roll out a small portion of dough at a time to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut in 1 inch strips and drop into 3 quarts chicken stock and chicken (boiling).
Cook 20 minutes.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease a 1 1/2 x 10-inch pie plate. Cook and stir beef and onion over medium heat until meat is browned.
Drain spread in plate.
Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour on top of meat in plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomato, sprinkle with cheese and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Combine chocolate chips, butter, Eagle brand milk in large microwave safe mixing bowl. Place in microwave on High for 3 minutes. Remove and stir. Add marshmallows and pecans and mix well. Pour into 9 X 13 greased pan and spread evenly. Cool and cut into squares.

title: hunker dip
directions: In skillet, brown the meat.
In casserole dish, layer half the beans, meat, onion and cheese.
Repeat layer with the other half of ingredients.
Pour enchilada sauce over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, then add liquid ingredients. Cook over medium heat on stove, stirring with a wooden spoon until thickened, stirring constantly.
Continue scraping the pan's bottom, moving the dough around until liquid has become solid. Turn out on counter and knead.

title: sparkling grape juice
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan, stirring; bring to a boil.
Boil mixture for 3 minutes, stirring often.
Add orange juice and grape juice.
Chill mixture.
Before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: carnation fudge
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
In saucepan, combine butter, milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil, over medium heat, for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into pan.
Cool and cut.

title: caribbean fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add pineapple juice and water to Jell-O.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in pineapple, bananas, walnuts and coconut. Chill until firm.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Drain.
Put 1/2 of macaroni in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Put in half of tomatoes next.
Add salt and pepper and layer of cheese slices.
Repeat with macaroni, tomatoes, salt and pepper and cheese on top layer.
Dot cheese slices with butter.
Pour 1/2 of tomato juice over casserole in one corner.
Pour in milk to fill 1/3 of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is brown and milk is bubbly.

title: rebecca's bread pudding
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Butter bread slices heavy on one side.
Stack in deep loaf dish or pan.
Between each layer of bread, sprinkle raisins.
Beat eggs until creamy.
Add sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add enough milk mixed with eggs to cover bread.
Bake at 350° until good and brown on top.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Pour tomatoes into a cake pan.
Add salt and pepper to season tomatoes.
Melt oleo in small saucepan.
Add flour to oleo and mix.
Drop by tablespoon onto tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: room mother's punch
directions: Prepare Kool-Aid according to package.
Add 7-Up; mix well. Place in freezer; check in 1 hour.
Ice should be forming around sides of container.
Stir well; check and stir every 15 minutes until thickened.

title: biscuit coffee cake
directions: Melt butter and put into a bowl.
Mix sugar and cinnamon into a separate bowl.
Put nuts in another bowl.
Dip each biscuit into butter, then sugar mixture and then nuts.
Place into a greased tube pan in layers.
Bake 1 hour.

title: oatmeal raisin chews
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and oats.
Mix well with wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend sugar with electric mixer set at medium speed.
Add butter and mix to form a grainy paste.
Scrape down sides of bowl, then add honey, vanilla and eggs.
Mix at medium speed until fully combined.
Add the flour mixture, raisins and walnuts and blend at low speed just until combined.
Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 18 to 22 minutes or until cookies are light golden brown. Immediately transfer cookies with a spatula to a cool flat surface.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Combine undrained pineapple and eggs.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Pour into a greased 1-1/2 quart baking dish.
Toss bread cubes in melted butter and place on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.
Yield 4 to 6 servings.
You may serve cold or warm dolloped with plain whipped topping or top with mixture of whipped topping and a little cherry pie filling.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
cornstarch and gelatin; add boiling water. Cook until
mixture
is	clear,	about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Cool.
Place
strawberries	into baked pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over berries and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.	Top with favorite topping and serve.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine and cook lentils, water, bouillon, celery, carrots and onion for 40 minutes.
Add potatoes; cook 20 more minutes.
Stir in tomatoes; cook until heated.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together and pour onto lightly floured paper and knead for just a minute. Put into bowl and cover.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Use as needed.
Keeps for at least 2 weeks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fry onion in 4 tablespoons oleo; add flour and water, stirring constantly.
When thick, add cheese.
Combine sauce with broccoli; add eggs.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cookie rocks
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Mix together dry ingredients. Add well
beaten
eggs alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, raisins and pecans.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 100 small cookies.

title: jacquies fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and vanilla.
Boil 2 minutes exactly. Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows; add chocolate, one at a time. Pour into greased sheet.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: frozen salad
directions: Blend together (in blender) cream cheese, yogurt and sugar. Stir in pineapple.
Spoon into 12 paper baking cups in muffin tins.
Cover and freeze.
Before serving, remove paper cups from salad.
Arrange on lettuce leaves and top with nuts, if desired. Let stand 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: black walnut sheet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Melt margarine and mix with cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients. Add buttermilk and eggs.
Bake in cookie sheet pan with edge at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocoanna bread
directions: Mix in order of list.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and press on bottom and sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: cactus with chile
directions: Cut meat to bite size.
Fry meat; then add chili and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cactus and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Eat with beans and flour tortillas.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In top of a double boiler, over boiling water, melt morsels with condensed milk and butter.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture. Drop onto wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: candy coated popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallow cream; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and salt. Pour mixture over popped corn and toss until well coated.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto wax paper and cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: new york roast beef
directions: Rub
oil all over roast.
Combine garlic and oregano and rub over the oiled roast.
Place in shallow baking pan with fat side up.
Bake at 350°, 20 minutes per pound.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion and potatoes and add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes. Ready to serve.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Beat pudding mix with milk well, then fold in prepared whipped topping.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with a single layer of whole graham crackers.
Spread half of pudding mixture evenly over crackers.
Cover with a second layer of crackers, then pour on the remaining pudding mix and a third layer of crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar, zucchini and oil.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture; mix well and add nuts or raisins.

title: white mountain surprise
directions: Mix crumbs, oleo and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Press into bottom of cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Place over crumbs.
Top with pie filling.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Prepare 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Peel and slice peaches. Combine sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Add to peaches and mix lightly.
Turn into pastry shell.
Pour whipping cream over top. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until firm. Chill well before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "buckeyes"
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, you'll have to use your hands to get it all mixed.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crunchy peanut butter balls
directions: Heat raisins and apple juice concentrate in a saucepan.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Pour raisins and juice into a blender and puree. Mix raisin puree and remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Add a few drops of water if necessary.
Shape the mixture into small balls. Eat as is or refrigerate overnight.
Makes about 30 small balls.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix in heavy skillet.
Cook until water disappears and nuts have sugared.
Separate quickly.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat with salt, pepper and onions; drain.
Add French's taco mix and 2 cups water.
Cook on medium heat until mixture is hot.
Let simmer on low heat, stirring when needed until mixture is thick.
Add drained corn and olives, if desired; heat.
Thaw and separate tortilla shells.
Grate each kind of cheese separately. Spray baking dish with Pam.
Fill each shell with a small amount of cheese (with peppers) and meat.

Roll filling into shell and lay in dish (side by side) and pour rest of meat sauce over rolled shells. Cover the top of shells with grated Cracker Barrel cheese; bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes until shells are hot and cheese has melted.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl in the order given.
Do not toss! Make the day before serving.

title: easy salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Place in greased 5 x 11-inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: crock-pot special
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high 4 hours or put in oven for 1 hour.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg yolks together thoroughly in saucepan.
Combine evaporated milk and water; stir into sugar mixture until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and let cool completely.
Arrange bananas in baked pie shell.
Cover with cool mixture.
Spread with whipped cream or whipped topping and refrigerate.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Put graham cracker crumbs in bottom of dish; dampen crumbs with melted butter.
Mix cream cheese, lemon juice and milk together in bowl and pour over crumbs.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
When chilled, put pie filling on top and serve or refrigerate.

title: chicken-stuffing casserole
directions: Combine soups and milk in a large bowl; mix well.
Stir in chicken and spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions. Spoon evenly over chicken mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes.

title: maple blended butter
directions: Cream butter and salt with electric mixer.
Add syrup 1 tablespoon at a time, beating after each addition until thoroughly blended.
Serve on waffles, toast, biscuits, muffins or gingerbread.
Makes about 3 cups butter.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order of ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serve as is.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients; knead on lightly floured board only until smooth. Roll very thin and cut into approximately 1-inch slices. Tear off bite size pieces and drop into boiling chicken broth (1 to 2 tablespoons margarine may be needed if chicken isn't fat enough). Cook, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes, until tender. Stir to keep from sticking.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with sauce.
Bake another 15 to 20 minutes. Serve.

title: garden vegetable mix and casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle or Dutch oven.
Fill sink with ice water.
Cook vegetables to a full boil over medium heat; remove from heat.
Cool quickly by setting kettle in sink of ice water.
Put vegetable mix into 4 (1-quart) freezer containers, leaving 1/2-inch space at top.
Seal, label and freeze.
Use within 6 months.
Makes about 15 cups of Mix.
Can also be used in Alphabet Vegetable Soup (See Salad/Soup section).

title: 3 day pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water for 24 hours.
Drain and cover with clear water for 3 hours (change water once each hour). Prepare juice and heat to boiling.
Pour hot juice over drained cucumbers and let set overnight.
Next morning, heat for 30 minutes and place in jars.
Seal while warm.

title: grandma samson's 4 baked beans
directions: Simmer all ingredients with the cans of beans.
Delicious alternative to basic baked beans!

title: clam sauce for over noodles
directions: In medium saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons margarine. Add diced onions, salt, pepper and flour; stir. Add clams and clam juice. Stir. Add milk and water; heat to a boil. Serve over noodles.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Put all ingredients in roaster and mix well. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cream cheese log
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and shape into log.
Roll in crushed pecans and chill.

title: mom and dad's favorite! "egg custard"
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk and heat to scalding.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir into milk.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: festive irish cream cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom of spring-form pan.

title: pecan caramel crispies
directions: In top of double boiler, place caramels and water.
Heat over boiling water, stirring often, until melted and smooth.
Combine cereal and pecans in large bowl.
Pour melted caramels over cereal and nuts.
Toss until well coated.
Pull apart and roll into balls the size of walnuts.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Cut cheese into 20 (1/2-inch) cubes.
Shred remaining cheese; set aside.
In bowl, mix with hands, beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion, salt, pepper and egg.
Make meatballs around cube of cheese, so cheese is in center of each.
In skillet, heat oil and lightly brown meatballs.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs, oil and Bisquick.
Add remaining ingredients and spread into pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Cut into bite size squares. Serve hot or cold.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk and butter in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add to milk.
Cover and remove from heat.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and salt. Stir hot milk and bread into egg mixture.
Add nutmeg, vanilla and raisins, mixing well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage, zucchini, skillet casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion, zucchini and corn in skillet.
Lower heat; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover with cheese and let set for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: beef n biscuit casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and green peppers; drain.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook wild rice as according to package directions; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve warm, adding cheese slices (Velveeta).
Mix together broccoli and can of mushroom soup. Serves 5 to 6.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Crumble ground beef; stir in onion.
Cook until beef is brown. Stir in tomato sauce, cheese, salt and instant rice. Cook awhile. I usually precook peppers awhile in microwave.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend all 4 ingredients together and chill.
Serve with Pineapple, bananas, strawberries, watermelon, peaches, apples, cantaloupe, etc.

title: hoti
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Set on low for 2 to 4 hours.
Serve with Cheddar cheese over boiled potatoes.

title: brazilian rice souffle
directions: Boil rice in slightly salted water and when done, strain and hold under cold tap water to wash off starch.
Drain thoroughly. Add chopped tomato to the tomato sauce and mix with rice.
Season to taste.
Add beaten egg yolks and peas and fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon, set bacon to drain; reserve 1 to 2 tsp. drippings. Put potatoes and water on, bring to a boil, simmer until done. Saute onions (and celery if desired) in bacon drippings until transparent, add seasonings.
Combine all of the above and add the half & half and the corn; simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour to meld flavors.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Add eggs, saving whites for meringue.
Add margarine, lemon and milk.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350°.
When nearly done, top with egg whites which have been stiffly beaten with 6 tablespoons sugar added.
You may also add 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar to egg whites.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Cook potatoes and then cool.
Mix all ingredients and combine thoroughly (mixture may be more moist than normal).

title: tomato salad
directions: Mix oil and vinegar well.
Add salt, hot sauce, lemon or lime juice and garlic powder to vinegar and oil mixture; mix well. Pour over tomatoes, onion and bell pepper.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: sesame chops
directions: Heat sauce and jam until jam melts.
Stir in sesame seed. Remove from heat.
Season chops with salt and pepper.

title: pickle relish
directions: Chop cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle salt over and let set overnight.
Drain.
Add all but celery seed and boil for 20 minutes.
Add celery seed and boil 5 minutes more.
Add green food coloring (11 drops) and seal.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: i can't believe it's zucchini
directions: Spread zucchini in a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish. Sprinkle garlic salt over zucchini.
Microwave margarine and onion for 2 minutes at full power.
Mix cream cheese with margarine-onion mixture until smooth.
Spread over zucchini. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place walnuts on top of mixture.
Blend next four ingredients until smooth.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: dream whip cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Prepare one small box jello and congeal slightly.

title: cavatelli and broccoli
directions: Cut crowns of broccoli off of head.
Chop cloves of garlic into small pieces.
In large frying pan, heat olive oil and garlic.
When garlic starts to brown, remove from heat.
When cooled, add chicken broth; reheat.
Cook cavatelli to desired tenderness.
Steam broccoli to desired tenderness.
Add cavatelli and broccoli to frying pan.
Add fresh cracked pepper to taste. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: italian coating mix for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in an airtight container. Makes 1 cup, enough to coat 3 pounds of chicken parts.

title: ham steaks
directions: Mix brown sugar and prepared mustard; spread on ham.
Boil water and vinegar and pour around ham slices.
Bake in 325° oven 1 hour, uncovered.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix and stir first 3 ingredients over low heat until gelatine dissolves.
Add 1 small can of crushed pineapple and juice of one lemon.
Chill in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Prepare 2 envelopes of Dream Whip by directions on package.
Add to gelatine mixture.
Crumble angel food cake in mixture and fold to combine. Pour in large pan.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Mix all remaining ingredients with meat, except tortillas, and cheese.
Cook 10 minutes.
Heat butter in skillet, and heat tortillas on both sides.
Spray dish, put tortillas on bottom of dish, then meat mixture.
Then cheese, then tortillas, and continue until cheese is on top.
Bake for 30 minutes for 350 degrees.

title: lemon soup
directions: Place the dried beans in a mixing bowl, cover them with water and let soak overnight.
Drain; turn into a large soup pot and re-cover with water.
Add the smoked ham hock and simmer slowly for about 4 hours until beans are cooked tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Just before serving, bruise the beans with a large spoon or ladle, enough to cloud the soup.
Serves 6.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Heat shortening or butter in a skillet.
Add onions and simmer until yellow.
Add ground beef and brown slightly.
Add remaining ingredients, then pour in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well together and put in Pyrex dish.

title: broiled scallop casserole
directions: Cover scallops with bread crumbs and little melted butter. Place in buttered casserole.
Mix rest of melted butter, white wine and lemon juice. Pour over scallops.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Check after 10 minutes.

title: johnnie marzetti
directions: In medium skillet, cook and stir meat, macaroni, onion and green pepper.
Cook until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until macaroni is tender, about 20 minutes.
Uncover and simmer until sauce is desired consistency.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lettuce-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Serves 12.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Saute hamburger until no longer pink.
Add onion and cook until done.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings to taste.
Heat thoroughly.
Layer tortillas in casserole with sauce, corn and cheese; ending with cheese and olives.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: easy veggie sauce
directions: Saute garlic, celery, carrots and whatever vegetables in olive oil, slowly.
Can cover pan until they are pretty tender.
When veggies are about done, add chopped basil and dump in the tomatoes.
When fresh tomatoes are in season use them.
Salt and pepper to taste; let simmer until ready to serve.
Serve over cooked pasta or split baked potatoes.
Serves 3 or 4 people.

title: ann's jewish brownies
directions: Mix and bake fudge brownie mix according to directions on box. Mix Baker's coconut long shreds with the Eagle Brand milk. Spread mixture over baked brownies. Cover entire top with chocolate fudge frosting. Very rich. Enjoy!

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: banana dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and butter together for 10 minutes. Spread over crumbs.
Slice bananas lengthwise; place on mixture. Drain the crushed pineapple; spread over bananas.
Cover with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and chill.

title: teri-bracken
directions: Brown roast on both sides in hot oil. (Use Dutch oven, if possible; otherwise, use a good heavy pot.) Combine teriyaki sauce, vinegar and 1 1/3 cups water. Pour over roast. Cover and simmer 1 hour. Turn roast and repeat for other side, 1 hour longer.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix 1/2 can water with cream of mushroom soup and spread on top of meat.
Mix 1/2 can of water with Cheddar cheese soup and spread on top.
Layer Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are brown and mixture is bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in floured and greased Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: uncle jay's homemade chili
directions: Lightly brown beef in skillet; add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes or 6 hours in crock-pot.

title: blueberry salad
directions: First Layer:
Make one box of Jell-O by directions; jell.

title: chocolate pan cake
directions: Put all ingredients in 13 x 9-inch baking pan and mix with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate 12 hours for best results.

title: spiced holiday nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl, mix cumin, chili powder, curry powder, garlic salt, cayenne pepper, ginger and cinnamon. Set aside.
Heat oil in a nonstick skillet over low heat.
Add spice mixture and mix well.
Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Place nuts in a bowl.
Scrape spice mixture onto nuts and toss well. Spread nuts in one layer on a baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes. Remove from oven. If desired, sprinkle with salt.
Cool for 2 hours. Store in airtight container.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Layer turkey in large casserole dish.
Mix broth, soups and vegetables; pour over turkey.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over first mixture.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: deep fried onions
directions: Soak sliced and separated onions in water and milk mixture for one hour in refrigerator.
Dredge or shake onions in flour and deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: white loaf bread
directions: Heat milk to boiling, stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour warm water into 3-quart bowl and sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture and 3 cups flour and beat until smooth;
add remainder of flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and brush top with melted margarine.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Punch down.
Turn out on lightly floured board and divide in half.
Form each into a smooth ball.
Place in greased loaf pans; cover and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 400° about 50 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat slowly in hot fat about 15 minutes.
Add onion and garlic the last few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water.
Add to meat.
Cover and simmer until almost tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Add tomatoes and green pepper.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Combine cornstarch, cold water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Bring to boil.
Cook and stir 5 minutes longer.
Remove garlic.
Serve with hot noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Dip a water glass or a meat tenderizer (mallet) in sugar and flatten the dough.
Bake in 300° oven until tan in color.
Let stand to cool before removing cookies.
Very short and crisp.

title: texas cheese casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix all ingredients, except Fritos and cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture in casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup crushed Fritos and 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange cream cake
directions: In a bowl combine cake and drink mix, eggs, water and oil. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.
Using a meat fork poke holes in cake and cool on a wire rack for 30 minutes. Dissolve 1 pkg. gelatin in boiling water and then stir in cold water.
Pour over cake.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
In a bowl combine milk, vanilla, pudding mix and remaining gelatin and beat on low for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes, fold into whipped topping and frost cake.
Refrigerate.
12 - 15 servings.

title: 3-cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook noodles in salted water; drain.
Cook onion in oleo until tender.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, pimentos, milk and basil.
Lay half of noodles in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with half of each, the sauce, cottage cheese, chicken, American and Parmesan cheeses. Repeat layers except for last 2 cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with rest of cheeses.
Bake 2 additional minutes.

title: pumpkin pie(sugar-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into crust.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: fage(irish bread)
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
Stir in caraway seed and raisins.
Add eggs and milk, stirring until well moistened.
The mixture will be quite thin.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Turn out loaves on cooling rack.
Butter tops and sprinkle with sugar while warm.
It is best served warm. Freezes well.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef and drain.
Stir in next 4 ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits into 1/2 circles and place around the edges of casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 25 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: cherry delight jello salad
directions: Mix jello in 1 cup boiling water and 1 cup pineapple juice. Stir in pie filling and pineapple.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Let jell. Mix pudding as directed on box and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on jello.

title: jello tapioca salad(could be pudding)
directions: Using liquid from can of oranges, add water to make 3 cups. Boil, dissolving Jell-O.
Add both puddings and cook until thick. Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in a 10 inch skillet.
Mix eggs with vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add to skillet and heat until hot.
Remove the skillet from the fire: add lettuce and onions. Toss 1 to 2 minutes, until lettuce is wilted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and fold together until mixed together well. Pour into mold or cake pan.
Freeze until firm.
May be cut into squares or slices.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Store in freezer.
If maraschino cherries are used, add several spoonfuls of the juice to make salad a pretty pink color.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese, lemon pepper, mushrooms and soup. Scoop onto crescent rolls.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with crushed bread crumbs.
Bake in buttered dish 12 to 18 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: burgundy mushrooms
directions: Clean and thoroughly dry mushrooms.
Combine water and lemon juice in covered saucepan and boil.
Melt in pan the margarine and saute onions about 5 minutes.
In bowl, add spices and bouillon to Burgundy; whisk until dissolved.
Add wine mixture to onions.
Simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add mushrooms to boiling lemon water; return to boil. Remove mushrooms from heat and thoroughly dry.
Add to wine sauce; stir until blended.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Put in flavoring; add flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll thin; cut with big biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water; add pineapple, strawberries and banana.
Pour half of mixture into dish.
Allow to set.
Cover with sour cream.
Add remaining jello on top.

title: turkey krunch(great idea for leftover turkey; yummy)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Top with a can of chow mein noodles and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until piping hot and bubbling.

title: wine cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and nutmeg.
Beat about 5 minutes; add wine last.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: macaroni, pizza style
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown beef and onion.
Mix all ingredients together, except Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and top with Mozzarella cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.
Let stand at room temperature for a few minutes before serving.

title: tomato, macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix together tomato sauce and pepper to taste.
Lightly spray cooking spray on baking dish.

title: date nut bread
directions: Put dates in saucepan.
Cover with water; bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Add butter, sugar and baking soda.
Stir well and cool slightly.
Add 3 cups flour, 1 egg, vanilla and nuts. Stir only until flour is blended.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Fold in flour, baking powder and milk.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, peanut butter and vanilla.
Form into balls. Place on a cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Chill overnight. Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin using a double boiler.
Keep hot in a pan of water while dipping balls into it.
Use toothpicks to dip the balls in the chocolate mixture.

title: white house pecan pie
directions: Put butter in a large mixing bowl and soften at room temperature.
Add sugar, corn syrup and vanilla; with a sturdy hand rotary beater or mixing spoon, beat until thoroughly blended.
Add eggs and beat gently, just until blended.
Fold in pecans and pour into pastry shells.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a saucepan melt margarine on stove.
Add sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Mix in whole and creamed corn.
Pour mixture into a baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all

ingredients, except potato chips and cheese. Blend well. Spoon into lightly greased 2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with potato chips. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: roasted garlic
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Peel some of the loose outer skin from garlic.
Place garlic heads in a small baking pan and brush with oil.
Bake until very tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients, except dressing.
Mix and put in casserole dish.
Mix 1/2 stick margarine and stuffing mix and put on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mennonite apple dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Cut apples in slices and dip.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Boil broth.
Add rest of ingredients and stir with a fork, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: busy day cupcakes
directions: Make cupcakes as directed on package.
Cool.
Spread top of each cupcake with sweet orange marmalade and top with about 10 miniature marshmallows.
Broil until marshmallows melt slightly and are golden brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and pour all the ingredients into a deep dish pie crust. Top with regular pie crust, leaving pan on.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove top pan and bake for 15 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, sugar, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well and pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: nut roll
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Set aside to rise. Sift flour and salt.
Cut in margarine.
Add yolks to yeast mixture and blend in flour.
Turn out on floured board and knead for 5 minutes.
Divide into 4 balls (let rise again).
Won't rise much.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well and bake in crust for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a quart jar.
Yields 1 quart.

title: easy potato chunks
directions: Cut potatoes into 1-inch chunks. Rinse and drain. Cover a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil. Drop potato chunks in center of foil. Add pepper, salt and margarine. Roll foil together and twist ends inward.
Place in center of pan. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: danny's peach pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers, peaches pudding mixture. Repeat layers. Finish with reserved Cool Whip-use a deep bowl. Chill overnight or several hours.

title: spicy shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer.
Refrigerate for 30 to 40 minutes before serving.
Serves approximately 12.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Parboil chicken breasts.
Mix cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup and mayonnaise together.
Put chicken breasts in dish and pour mixture over chicken.
Place crumbs of Stove Top dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apfelkuppenkuchen (ap-fel-kopp-en-ku-chen)(apple cake)
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, granulated sugar, salt and dry yeast.
Add margarine (or butter) and very warm water and beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups more flour or enough to make a stiff batter.
Cover; let rise in warm place free from draft until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: jean's blueberry dessert(low carb or health conscience recipe)
directions: Make vanilla pudding according to directions. Tear angel food cake into small pieces. Alternate layers in large bowl: pudding/cake/blueberry/Cool Whip. End up with Cool Whip on top. Decorate with fresh blueberries if desired.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion in oleo until tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking.
I boil my broccoli for a few minutes before adding to milk and soup mixture.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Add mashed bananas and juices.
Freeze. Pour ginger ale over mixture before serving.
Serves 60.

title: seven up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Combine well.
Add flour.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour mixture into well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower oven to 350°.
Bake about 20 minutes more.

title: citrus-honey chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Place each breast half between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
Working from center to edges, pound with the flat side of a meat mallet to 1/8-inch thickness.
Remove plastic wrap.

title: eggless and butterless cake
directions: Stew the raisins in the water for 15 minutes, then add the remaining ingredients, except walnuts. Add the walnuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Pour 1/2 of mixture into Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 of brown sugar and cinnamon mixture on batter.
Pour rest of batter in pan and top with remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes or more before taking out of pan.

title: double pie crust
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening and stir until dissolved. Add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and chill approximately 20 minutes.
Roll between 2 sheets of wax paper.

title: sangria
directions: Into
large pitcher, pour lemon juice, orange juice and sugar. Stir
in
remaining
ingredients.	Pour
into glasses, making sure each person gets some fruit.

title: apple grape punch
directions: Combine apple juice and water.
Toss apple slices in lemon juice to prevent browning.
Arrange grapes and apple slices in an attractive design in 5-cup ring mold.
Pour apple juice/water mixture into mold to partially cover fruit (about 3/4 cup) and freeze.
When frozen, add remaining mixture.
Freeze completely.

title: potato salad, sweet and sour
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar in small saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Transfer to large bowl and add green onion, salt, pepper, catsup and mayonnaise.
Add potatoes, celery and toss to coat.
Chill before serving.
Makes 4 servings.
Calories: 319; Fat: 11 grams; Cholesterol: 30 mg.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In one-quart casserole, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon Bisquick or flour and cinnamon.
In bowl, mix remaining Bisquick or flour with brown sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cobbler is ready when toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cukes.
Cut up onions and peppers.
Put in glass or plastic container with salt.
Stir sugar, vinegar and celery seed. Heat well to dissolve sugar.
Add mix to cukes, onions and peppers.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 1 year.

title: chicken with black beans and yellow rice
directions: Prepare rice. Set aside. Heat oil and add chicken. Cook 3 minutes each side until browned. Remove, reserving drippings in skillet. Set aside. Saute onion and garlic in hot drippings, 3 to 4 minutes. Add orange juice, stirring to loosen particles from bottom of skillet. Stir in beans and broth. Add chicken and bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until done. Serve over rice.

title: best ever blondies
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Line bottom and sides with waxed paper.
Grease waxed paper.
In a small saucepan, cook and stir butter and white baking bar over low heat until melted (mixture may separate).
Set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light.
Add butter mixture and vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 minutes, or until top is golden.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Loosen edges and invert.
Remove waxed paper; invert again. Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: stuffed pickles
directions: Cut ends from pickles.
Scoop out seedy pulp.
Fill pickles with cheese spread.
Chill several hours.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Makes about 4 dozen slices.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Cut Velveeta into chunks and put into crock-pot.
Cook ground beef in skillet and drain.
When Velveeta is melted, add meat, refried beans and salsa.
Stir until mixed well.
Add a little milk, 1/4 cup at a time, until mixture is thin enough.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients except for bread. Soak bread in mixture. Cook on lightly oiled griddle over low heat. Turn frequently to brown evenly.

title: red potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. Stir in potatoes, celery and onions. Cover and chill.

title: cranberry-apple waldorf
directions: In a large bowl mix gelatine with sugar.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Add cranberry juice.
Stir in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix strawberries and Jell-O and heat until warm or Jell-O dissolves.
Set back to cool.
Mix pudding mix with milk.
Stir until thick.
Add sour cream and mix.
Fold in 3/4 of Cool Whip.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Grease large cookie sheet. Slice cookie dough into 1-inch slices.
Place on cookie sheet to form 1 large cookie, pinching together.

If necessary, cover with wax paper and gently use rolling pin to even out. Leave 3 to 4-inches around edge because dough will spread while cooking. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool completely. Mix cream cheese with sugar and spread over cookie. Slice fresh fruit and place on top of cream cheese. Chill.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Cream thoroughly.
Mix flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Divide coconut in half.
Use half in pie and save half to sprinkle on top of meringue.
Mix flour and sugar well.
Add milk slowly, stirring well to blend.
Add well-beaten egg yolks.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Place in double boiler and cook until thick. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and coconut.
Brown in oven.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in loaf pan about 45 minutes or a tube pan for 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.

title: poor man's cheese souffle
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Put in Pyrex dish.
Layer with 1/2 of cheese.
Put another layer of bread, then rest of cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together with seasonings.
Pour over, cover and refrigerate overnight.
(Push bread down with spoon if it floats.) Bake at 300° for 45 minutes (take off foil for last 15 minutes).

title: quiche supreme
directions: Bake pie shell for 10 minutes at 400°.
In butter saute onion, mushrooms and broccoli until soft.
Spoon into pie shell. Sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
Beat eggs in small bowl until frothy.
Stir milk into eggs and pour over vegetables and cheese. Top with bacon.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then lower to 350° and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put 1/3 to 1/2 cup hot chocolate mix to 1 cup boiling water.
Store in tight container.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown well in hot fat in skillet.
Turn down heat, add water and simmer 45 minutes, turning once.
Add more water if necessary.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Fry bacon until rubbery and wrap around each nut.

title: sugar walnuts
directions: Spread walnuts in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch ungreased jelly roll pan. Thoroughly stir together the sugar, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave as directed on package.
Melt together, in a medium saucepan, on low heat, both cheeses and soup.
Stir in broccoli and cook for a few more minutes, until evenly heated.
Serve as a dip with Fritos.
Also great on baked potatoes.
(May also be cooked in a crock-pot.)

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Add hot dogs and simmer 15 minutes.

title: marinated cauliflower
directions: Prepare cauliflower as directed on package; drain.
Meanwhile, prepare salad dressing mix with vinegar, water and salad oil as directed.
Lay lettuce leaves in bottom of bowl.
Put cauliflower over lettuce and pour 1/2 cup salad dressing over vegetables. Chill at least 3 hours.
Garnish with minced scallions and crumbled cooked bacon if desired.
Makes about 2 cups or 3 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Drop cookies by teaspoonfuls about
2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: seven layer salad
directions: *Can substitute lite Italian salad dressing mix for these ingredients.

title: easy eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in chunks and boil until tender.
Drain and mash with butter.
Add slightly beaten egg, milk, grated cheese and crumbs.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add and mix well.
Dot with cheese and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour into a baking dish.
Sprinkle on topping and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: In large bowl, crumble muffins and bread.

Saute sausage, onions and celery in 1 teaspoon oil until sausage is brown. Drain; pat dry with paper towel and crumble into a small bowl. Combine slightly beaten eggs, evaporated milk and chicken broth. Pour over bread crumb mixture; let stand until liquid is absorbed. Add sausage mixture and spices; stir well.
Spoon into greased pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
If dressing looks as if it is drying out, cover during baking.

title: bread pudding with rum sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wet the bread and squeeze the water out of it.
Melt the butter and mix with all other ingredients.
Pour mixture into a well-greased 4 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours.
The pudding will rise in the first hour.
After an hour, remove pan from oven and stir the mixture to tighten it. Return to the oven for the second hour of cooking.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Prepare and cook 5 cups shredded cabbage (be sure to add 2 tablespoons vinegar or lemon juice to the salted water).

title: mashed potato pie
directions: Mash cottage cheese with back of large spoon to make smooth. Beat mashed potatoes into cottage cheese.
Beat in sour cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Stir in scallions.
Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes until brown on top.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Cut vegetables in circles.
Cover with salt and ice cubes.
Let stand 2 hours or overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Put in large jar. Cover with vinegar mix.
Shake well, don't have to seal.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cheese potato bread (italian)
directions: Soften compressed yeast in 1/2 cup scalded milk; cool to lukewarm.
If dry yeast used, dissolve in 1/4 cup lukewarm water as directed on package; decrease amount of scalded milk to 1/4 cup.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt. Combine potatoes, melted butter or margarine, cheese and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat until well combined.
Blend in yeast-milk mixture and dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Knead on well floured board until smooth and satiny, 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise in a warm place (85° to 90°) until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough by plunging fist in center.
Knead gently on floured board about 2 minutes. Shape into a long roll and fit into well-greased 9-inch ring mold. Pinch ends together to seal.
Let rise in warm place until light, about 30 minutes.
Bake in 375° oven 25 to 35 minutes.

title: no fat fries
directions: Cut potatoes into fry size strips.

Put taters in bowl and sprinkle with some black pepper and either cayenne pepper, paprika or chili powder. Pour beaten egg white over fries and toss to coat evenly. Place fries on a cookie sheet that's lightly coated with nonstick spray. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients. Mix syrup and hot water.
Add dry ingredients and liquid alternately.
Bake in floured pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except buns.
Spread on half of a bun.
Broil for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: "sausage rolls"
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Put pork sausage, egg, onion, herbs, breadcrumbs and milk into large bowl and mix well.
Sprinkle flour onto kitchen bonch top.
Roll out pastry sheets to 14-inch length and cut into 3 x 3-inch widths.
Brush 1 edge of each with water. Roll sausage mixture into long sausage shape and lay in middle of pastry strip (lengthwise).
Turn edge of pastry over sausage and turn again onto water-brushed edge (should be underneath).
Repeat with remaining pastry strips and filling.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook grits according to directions.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients except for 1/4 cup of cheese.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Can be fixed the night before.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Add all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove from oven and mash with potato masher.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Cut dill pickles into spears.
Mix with sugar, onion, celery seed, vinegar, horseradish and garlic (chopped fine).
Put in jar and refrigerate.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Put 2/3 of crumbs in bottom of dish.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Spoon mixture into pan over crumbs and spread.
Put pineapple over cream mixture.
Whip the whipping cream and put on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle pecans over cream, then cover with remaining crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator a couple of hours before serving.
Cut into 2-inch squares and decorate with a nut or cherry.

title: pastel banana bobs
directions: Prepare bananas as directed for Chocolate Banana Bobs.
In top of double boiler over hot water, melt butter in milk.
Stir in frosting mix (dry) until smooth.
Heat over boiling water 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Dip bananas into mixture, spreading over pieces.
Roll in coconut.
Place on waxed paper-covered baking sheet.
Chill until firm.
Do not freeze. Makes 16 Banana Bobs.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add eggs and melted chocolate. Beat in flour and chopped nuts. Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar, egg & molasses. Blend in remaining ingredients, except sugar. Cover and chill for 1 hour. Heat oven to 375 degrees. Shape dough by rounded tsp. into balls. Dip top in granulated sugar. Place balls sugared side up three inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 10-12 minutes or just until set. Immediately remove from baking sheet. Yield 4 dozen.

title: shrimp and rice dinner
directions: Combine rice, seasoning, water and 2 tablespoons butter in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a vigorous boil.
Add asparagus or broccoli.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until water is absorbed (about 5 minutes).

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.

title: choco-cherry cake(serves 15 to 20)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir by hand to mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (may take longer).

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix salad dressing according to package directions and pour over the salad.
Toss and refrigerate.
The longer it sits, the better it gets.

title: granny's chess pie
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes or until done in a 350° oven.
Top with pecans, if desired.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika on top for a festive look.
Easy and really special.
Serves 12.

title: broiled crabmeat canapes
directions: In large bowl, blend together softened butter and cheese.
Stir in the mayonnaise, salts and crabmeat.
Spread on muffin halves. Cut each muffin into four pieces.
Spread on cookie sheet and freeze.
Place in plastic bags until ready to serve.
At serving time, broil until brown and bubbly.
Yields 48 hors d'oeuvres.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes with sugar, milk, egg, 3 tablespoons butter and vanilla.
With wooden spoon, stir to break up potatoes, but do not mash.
Place in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine brown sugar and flour; cut in butter until you have coarse crumbs. Stir in nuts and sprinkle mixture over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Slice onion and separate in rings.
Cut other vegetables in bite-size pieces.
Pour salad dressing over vegetables and let set for 1 hour or longer.

title: baked wontons
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, combine soy sauce and sesame oil.
Place wonton wrappers on nonstick baking sheet.
With pastry brush, brush wontons evenly with soy mixture.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Serves 4.

title: benny's batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use the batter to make crepes, waffles or pancakes.
This batter has a light, creamy and unique taste.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add the egg to the milk and add to dry ingredients.
Melt shortening in pan you plan to bake bread in.
Pour melted shortening in bread mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bacon-wrapped hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs in half; wrap with bacon, securing with toothpicks.
Place in crock-pot; top with brown sugar and cook on low for a couple of hours.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Put marshmallow cream in a bowl.
Put sugar and water in pan. Bring to boil and then to a soft ball.
Pour this over the marshmallow cream and beat until glossy.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm (about 45 to 60 minutes).

title: hot rolls
directions: Sift together 3 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and the yeast.
To this, add 2 cups warm water.
Mix well.
Add the melted Crisco; mix, then add the egg and beat.
Then add the 3 remaining cups of flour; mix well.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, milk and 1 package of soup; form into balls. Cook until brown.
Drain.
Add other package of soup to 1 cup water and pour over meatballs.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad(microwave time 27 to 33 minutes)
directions: Pierce potatoes with fork.
Place potatoes in 1/4 cup water in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 14 to 16 minutes, stirring after 6 minutes, until tender.
Drain.
Cool about 15 minutes or until cool enough to handle.
Slice potatoes and return to casserole.

title: elaine's chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat with electric beater until it gets thick.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in small amount of fat until tender.
Add meat; brown lightly.
Add vegetables and soup; heat to boiling.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (until biscuits are done).

title: mimi's pink salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to chilled mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: fruit bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ingredients as pie crust (it's crumbly).
Spray-grease a 9 x 12-inch pan and put half of mixture in; press on bottom.
Pour filling over this and spread out. Sprinkle rest of first mixture on top and tamp lightly.
Cook 20 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: summer punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator.

title: avocado soup
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups of the chicken broth and the remaining ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on medium speed until smooth.
Stir remaining broth into avocado mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled, about 2 hours.
Garnish with sour cream and paprika or avocado slices, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow all ingredients to come to room temperature.
Mix well. Shape into 3 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts (or parsley). Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate.

title: coconut pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix together egg and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla and coconut. Melt butter and mix.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cook pies on cookie sheet.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, oil and vanilla.
Sift flour with dry ingredients and add to sugar and butter mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 7 dozen cookies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients in
a pot; bring to a boil.
Pour in a casserole dish with pie crust.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.

title: csirke paprikash(chicken paprika)
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in 3 tablespoons butter or margarine in a large skillet until tender.
Stir in paprika and vinegar. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Add chicken to vegetable mixtere in skillet and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Add water and bouillon granules.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
