Prepare noodles according to package directions; drain well.
Toss noodles with 1 tablespoon melted butter and parsley.
To serve, arrange chicken over noodles, top with sauce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: eclair cake
directions: Boil water and add margarine. Continue boiling just until margarine melts.
Remove from heat and add flour. Stir until mixture leaves sides of the pan. Beat eggs in one at a time.
Pour batter into a greased 12 x 15-inch pan and bake in a 400° oven for about 30 minutes.
Set cake aside to cool.

title: broccoli with lemon garlic(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cut broccoli lengthwise into pieces.
Steam until crisp and tender.
Melt butter with lemon juice and garlic in small saucepan over medium-low heat.
Pour over broccoli and serve.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix gelatin, 3 tablespoons sugar, salt, 1 packet Butter Buds, 1/2 cup pineapple juice, milk and egg yolks in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water and cook, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly. Cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, saut the onion, green pepper and butter.
Add in remaining ingredients, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil. Let stand for a few minutes and serve.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil in 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute; remove from heat. Beat in eggs, one at a time, continue beating until smooth.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet (or 1/4 cupful if want bigger cream puffs).
Bake until puffed and golden, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool away from draft.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Spread raw ground beef and onion in bottom of casserole dish. Layer beans and potatoes over meat.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Chop all fruits; dredge lightly with flour and set aside. Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs until foamy; add to sugar mixture, blending well.
Sift flour with spices, cocoa and soda; add to mixture, together with the dredged fruit and strong coffee. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Do not place too close together, as they will spread some.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 18 minutes, until they become a rich biscuit color. Cool; store in jars.
Makes 10 dozen cookies.
The longer they stand, the better they are.

title: key lime pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lime rind and juice. Pour slowly into beaten egg yolk, stirring constantly.
Add condensed milk and bitters.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Add food coloring.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Garnish with lime slices or prepared Dream Whip whipped topping if desired.

title: cafe vienna
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in a tight container. `Note:
Use 2 rounded teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut tops off bell peppers.
Chop onions and garlic and add to ground beef.
Stir in black pepper.
Spoon into bell peppers and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Put buttered Bread in an 8 inch square baking dish, buttered side down. Cover with a thin layer of Applesauce. Sprinkle with Cinnamon.

title: creamy peach ice cream
directions: Mix peaches, sugar and lemon juice.
Turn into ice cream freezer can.
Mix in whipping cream.
Fill can to 3/4 full with half and half.
Freeze until firm.

title: trash
directions: Melt margarine on low heat and add all other seasonings, mixing well.
Pour cereals and nuts in brown paper bag.
Pour small amount of margarine mix over cereal and stir.
Keep doing this until all sauce is used, stirring cereal each time. Put in large pan and bake in 250° oven for about 30 minutes.
Stir often.

title: turkey or chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Into a buttered casserole dish, place alternate layers of noodles and chicken.
Mix milk and chicken soup.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Make batter as directed, except stir in 1/4 teaspoon soda into mix before adding water and eggs.
Use only 3/4 cup water.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed on mixer.
Fold 3/4 cup applesauce into batter.
If desired, add 1/3 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in oblong or layer pans as directed.
Frost with Butter Icing.

title: ground turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan, which has been lined with foil, for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Grease foil.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in 4 cups water until tender. Scald milk. Melt margarine in small skillet, add parsley. Stir in flour and seasoning. Add to milk and cook until slightly thickened. Combine with potatoes. Stir until well blended.

title: scallop florentine
directions: Cook spinach.
Melt margarine; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add cream, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in scallops, spinach, mushrooms and mustard; heat thoroughly.
Serve on toast points or patty shells.
Serves 6.

title: pot roast with vegetables
directions: Heat margarine in Dutch oven.
Add meat and brown well, then sprinkle with salt and pepper; add water.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour more.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter and gradually add sugar, beating all the time. Beat in eggs, one at a time; add flour mixture. Add lemon juice. Put batter in greased and floured pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in 325° oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and orange.
Mix with sugar and let set overnight.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients to jello in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set. Great with turkey and dressing.

title: almond black-out pie
directions: Prepare instant pudding according to package directions, reducing milk by 1/2 cup.
Stir in almond extract.
Pour filling into prepared crust and chill 5 minutes.
Spread top with whipped topping; sprinkle with miniature chocolate chips.
Garnish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican white cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese and put in sauce pan.
Over medium-low heat, add just enough milk to melt the cheese to the desired consistency, stirring constantly so cheese doesn't burn.
Blend in finely chopped jalapenos (or green salsa) to taste.

title: red velvet sheet cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in small bowl.
Blend egg in mixing bowl with fork; add oil and blend again.
Add dry ingredients and mix until smooth at medium speed.
Add buttermilk, food coloring, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into greased, floured pans or loaf pan. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Use desired frosting.

title: meatball macaroni supper
directions: Combine beef with next 7 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in oil.
Drain fat.
Combine paste, water, sugar and salt.
Add to meatballs in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Heat 5 minutes more.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: french-style green beans
directions: Cook green beans as directed.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup, egg, sour cream and mayonnaise and mix with green beans. Put grated cheese over top, bread cubes over cheese and Parmesan cheese over bread cubes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add onion and rice. Simmer until onions are transparent.
Add 1 can consomme and 1 can water. Add mushrooms and bring to a boil.	Arrange browned chops in bottom of buttered casserole and pour rice mixture on top.	Bake at 350° for 45-55 minutes.	Serves 6.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all in blender and enjoy.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine strawberry juice and marshmallows in a double boiler, heat until melted and cool.
Add cream cheese, salad dressing, pineapple and sliced strawberries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mandarin orange vinaigrette
directions: Place drained orange slices into blender and mix well. Add vinegar, spices and sugar. Blend and pour in oil. Refrigerate/shake before serving.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first four ingredients.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes on top of stove.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Spoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to butter mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Chill before baking.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: texas slush
directions: In pan boil and cool - 7 cups water and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
In another pan boil and cool 2 cups water and 4 tea bags.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together in a heavy saucepan both sugars, light cream and chocolate.
Cook until forms a soft ball, when a drop is put in cool water or 234°.
Stir just enough to keep from sticking. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; do not stir again until lukewarm, then beat until it starts to lose its shine.
Add pecans.
Drop on wax paper or onto foil.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix and let set at least 3 hours before serving.
Can be used on salads, chip dip or veggie dip.

title: peach pie
directions: Slice 1 layer of peaches in pie crust.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450° and for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into bottom of pan; bake until golden brown.
Cream milk, cheese, lemon juice and vanilla; spread on top of cookie.
Place fruit on top of cream cheese mixture.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and orange juice in pan; simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over fruit and chill in refrigerator.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add soda to pulp, then add to creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add milk and vanilla and mix.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Check after 1 hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Measure and mix dry ingredients, then add eggs, milk and oil. Beat with mixer until blended well.
Cook on 400° grill or in skillet with a little Crisco in it.
These are delicious.

title: beef and noodles(6 servings)
directions: Saut the beef, onion and garlic in oil. When browned, add the mushrooms, seasonings and soup. Simmer until the beef is tender. Serve over the cooked noodles.

title: peanut brittle with chocolate
directions: Boil together sugars, syrup, salt and water until the mixture reaches 300° on a candy thermometer.
Add butter and baking soda, stirring until just mixed.
Add nuts.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle immediately with chocolate, either leaving in pieces or smoothing with spatula.

title: betty miller's best fruitcake ever
directions: Mix fruit, coconut, nuts and flour in a very large bowl.
Set aside.
In another large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, syrup and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour this mixture into a 10-quart baking pan or kettle.
Add fruit and nut mix; blend thoroughly.
Bake in 400° oven, removing from oven every 5 minutes to scrape down sides and stir, for a total of 1 1/2 hours.
Use a timer and mark off each 5 minutes so as not to forget.
At end of baking, while still hot, mold fruitcake into greased foil bread pans.
Chill and serve or freeze.
Makes approximately 8 cakes.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef in the melted butter.
Drain.
Stir in soup mix, beans, ketchup, water, mustard and vinegar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: fruit roll
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well. Divide into 3 equal portions. Roll each into an 11-inch log. Roll each log in powdered sugar and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate several hours or until firm. Cut into 1/2-inch slices, reshaping slices, if necessary. Yield: about 5 dozen slices.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Stir together and bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard, celery seed and salt.
Pour over cabbage and onion while hot.
Wait 24 hours before serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift 2 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix until dry ingredients are dampened. Mix berries with 2 tablespoons flour; fold in berries.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a preheated hot oven (400°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with lots of butter.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients three times; and alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into four greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325 degrees until cake tests done.
Top springs back when touched lightly.
Cool and frost with filling (recipe and directions below).

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage lightly; drain.
Saute onion, garlic, celery and green pepper in sausage drippings.
Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix together and pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: golden anniversary punch
directions: Follow directions on can for lemonade and for frozen orange juice.
Add pineapple juice and apricot juice. Chill and serve.

title: grated sweet potato casserole
directions: To the grated sweet potatoes, add the sugar, butter, pecans, nutmeg, cinnamon, vanilla and enough milk to moisten. Bake at 400° for one hour or until mixture thickens. Remove from oven and cover with marshmallows. Return to oven to brown.

title: turkey and dressing casserole
directions: Put turkey pieces in bottom of baking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix chicken soup, broth and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix together 1 bag dressing mix and just enough broth to moisten. Spoon over other ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 5 more minutes.

title: easy crab dip
directions: Drain crab meat and pick out any small pieces of shells that may be present.
Place cream cheese on serving dish and sprinkle crab meat on top.
Pour cocktail sauce over cheese and crab meat. Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: cherry pineapple dessert(serves 6)
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple in baking dish.
Top with cake mix from box.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and reduce temperature to 350° for an additional 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes with stick of butter, onion, soup, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Top with corn flake mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Beat strawberries, lemon juice and egg whites.
Mix at high speed for 10 to 12 minutes, until stiff peaks form.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, bacon and mushrooms.
Put in casserole.
Put tomatoes on top.
Mix cheese soup with 1/2 can water or milk and pour over mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with more bacon, if desired.

title: hunter's meal
directions: Brown beef, add peppers and onions; saute.
Add mushrooms after excess fat has been drained off.
Add tomatoes, cream of mushroom soup, tomato soup, and egg noodles.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and quarter eggplant.
Boil in salt water until tender. Soak bread in milk.
Mash eggplant with bread.
Add beaten eggs, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in cheese.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: Drain corn. (Boil for 20 minutes if using home canned corn.) Combine corn, milk, eggs, onion, pepper and 3/4 cup cheese.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter and remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut and polish sausage
directions: Strain sauerkraut.
Add sauerkraut to pan; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Boil for 30 minutes and strain.
Fry onion in butter or margarine.
Cut through sauerkraut with knife and add to onion mix.
In separate pan, boil sausage in enough water to cover for 1/2 hour.
Remove and place on dish.
When cool enough to handle, cut in slices.
Add to onion and sauerkraut mixture; mix thoroughly.
Season to taste and enjoy!
Mashed potatoes can be served with this.

title: paul prudhomme's new orleans bread pudding with lemon sauce and
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs on high speed for 3 minutes.
Add sugar, vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon and butter and beat on high until well blended.
Beat in milk, then stir in raisins and pecans. Place bread cubes in a greased loaf pan.
Pour egg mixture over cubes and toss until bread is soaked.
Let sit about 45 minutes, patting bread down occasionally.
Place in preheated 350° oven. Immediately lower heat to 300° and bake 40 minutes.
Increase oven to 425° and bake until pudding is well browned and puffy, about 15 to 20 minutes more.
To serve, put 1 1/2 tablespoons warm Lemon Sauce in each dessert dish, then spoon in 1/2 cup hot Bread Pudding and top with Chantilly Cream.

title: calico marinated salad
directions: Let salad set overnight.

title: ripe olive casserole
directions: Prepare pasta according to directions on package.
Cook corn and drain.
Brown meat with onion and bell pepper; drain fat.
Add all other ingredients, except corn chips, and bring to a boil. Then place into casserole dish and top with corn chips.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 325° until firm.

title: summer broccoli salad
directions: Parboil broccoli in salted water.
Cool and drain.
Chop into 1/2-inch lengths.
Mix and chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Mix again and let stand in refrigerator for another 24 hours.
Form into logs. Bake at 250° for 6 to 7 hours.

title: casserole dill bread
directions: In a large bowl mix 1/4 cup flour, sugar, salt, instant minced onion, dill seed, soda and undissolved yeast.
Add softened butter.
Gradually add very hot tap water and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric beater.
Scrap bowl occasionally.

title: no-fuss pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides over medium-high heat.
Place in shallow baking pan (not glass), side by side.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon evenly over chops.
Cover pan well with foil.
Place in oven; turn heat control to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes; remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer or until chops are tender.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat whites of eggs until stiff and fold into mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan.
Do not grease pan. Cover bottom with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients.
Add flour and baking powder. Mix. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Combine egg, milk, oil, raisins, nuts and pineapple. Mix. Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Stir until just moistened. Bake in 2 greased bread tins for about an hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cut up chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread soups over chicken.
Add optional carrots and peas.
Add broth over this.
Mix melted margarine, Bisquick and milk together. Beat until well mixed.
Pour over chicken and gently spread around.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until brown crust forms.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Preparation Time:
30 minutes.

title: exotic celery
directions: Cook celery in a small amount of boiling water for 8 minutes; drain well.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa making sure there are no lumps of cocoa.
Add other ingredients except vanilla.
Bring to a boil; do not let it boil more than one minute (I usually stir it for about 30 seconds).
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Add first 5 ingredients in pan and start to boil on low heat. Add biscuits pinched a little bit at a time.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Toss with Poppy Seed Dressing.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onions, raisins and bacon together.
Blend salad dressing, sugar and vinegar thoroughly. Fold dressing into vegetable mixture and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: elegant chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into casserole dish.
Put the 1 cup cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: colleen's fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Turn heat down and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, Karo, oleo and vanilla.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in buttered 9 x 2 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: easy kolacky
directions: Blend sugar and margarine; add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and salt, 1/4 at a time, and mix well.
Dough will be stiff. Refrigerate overnight.
Separate into 4 sections and roll out on floured surface.
Cut into shape and place on ungreased cookie sheets and place 1/4 teaspoon of filling in center.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar while warm.

title: cajun chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger, then add other ingredients.
Cover and let simmer about 30 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: ruffled potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add vanilla.
Add crushed potato chips alternately with flour.

title: trip fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large saucepan, cook filling as directed on package.
Blend cake mix (dry) into hot pudding.
Beat by hand or mixer 1 to 2 minutes. Pour in pan.
Sprinkle batter with chocolate pieces and nuts. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Thinly slice tomatoes.
Beat egg, salt and milk.
Dip tomatoes slices in egg batter.
Coat with fish fry.
Fry in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: hush puppies #1
directions: Mix above ingredients and spoon into hot oil. Cook until browned.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs until well blended. Blend in dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add cinnamon and vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle topping over cake.
Bake at 325° approximately 45 minutes.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix Good Seasons Italian dressing according to directions. Pour over linguine and vegetables.
Sprinkle on 3/4 bottle of McCormick Salad Supreme.
Toss to mix ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
"Will keep for a week."

title: veal parmesan
directions: Combine flour and seasonings; coat chops.
Mix crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chops in egg, then in crumb mixture.
Brown slowly in hot olive oil.
Place a slice of Mozzarella cheese on top of each chop.
Pour sauce (one 8 ounce can of herbed tomato sauce) over it and sprinkle with 1 1/2 tablespoons oregano.
Cover and simmer 50 minutes.

title: aunt may's salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs and mix into sugar and flour.
Add mustard; salt and pepper to taste.
Slowly add vinegar and water to egg mixture; stir continuously until boiling.
If you like a stronger dressing, add more vinegar than water.

title: carrot ring
directions: Grease and flour ring mold.
Combine all ingredients and pour into ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in water bath.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, garlic salt and pepper.
Dip each piece of chicken in butter, then roll in dry mixture.
Place in greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: sixty minute whole grain french bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in water and let sit for 5 minutes.
Stir in whole wheat flour with wooden spoon and blend well.
Add salt and stir again.
Gradually mix in white flour, half a cup at a time, until the dough loses its wet look and becomes a floury, shaggy mass.
Preheat oven to 425°.
After flouring your hands, remove dough from bowl and knead for a minute or two, until dough firms up.
Lightly oil one large or two small French bread pans or a cookie sheet.
Shape the dough into one or two baguettes or a boule (ball) and place in pans or on sheet.

title: three cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley and pecans (a food processor makes a very smooth cheese; an electric mixer will leave some discernible individual ingredients). Toss parsley with pecans and blend half into cheese mixture.
Form cheese into a ball and roll in remaining parsley mixture until well coated.

title: brownie delight
directions: Make brownies according to the directions on the box. Undercook slightly.
Let cool.
Mix together one 8 ounce container Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of the brownies.
Prepare pudding and put on top of the cheese.
Spread second container of Cool Whip for the top layer.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Place sausage meat (thoroughly broken up) in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle rice over it.
Add onion, tomatoes, mustard and salt.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Drain off any excess fat.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook and drain noodles; set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil; add ground beef and cook until brown.
Drain beef and put it back in the skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce and heat.
Add 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Stir constantly until well blended.
Mix meat sauce and noodles together and pour into a large baking dish.
Top with remaining cheeses.
Cook in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni.
Fry and chop hamburger.
Saute onion in meat; drain off fat from fried-out hamburger.
Dry water off cooked macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until fairly stiff, then add salt; continue beating, adding sugar slowly, beating until stiff and glossy.
Liquid add ins can be added while beating; others you may fold in after beating.
Spoon tablespoons onto cookie sheets, peaking at top of each spoonful.
Put into oven and turn off!!
Do not open oven until it is cold to the touch on oven door!

title: tamale dip
directions: Mash all together and heat in crock-pot.
Serve with chips.

title: people chow
directions: Melt butter, chips and peanut butter.
Microwave 2 minutes. Blend well.
Pour over cereal and coat well.
Put 1 cup powdered sugar in bag; add cereal, then remaining sugar.
Shake well. Cool.

title: claire's chickie-egg-nose
directions: Use a small glass and cut the middle out of your bread like you would when making biscuits.
Save your circle of bread.
Place the bread in a warm skillet with melted butter.
Then crack your egg in the middle of the hole.
Let cook about 2 minutes, then flip.
Butter both sides of the middle you cut out and saved. Place in skillet; brown on both sides.
When egg is ready, serve circle with jelly!

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and rinse in cool water.
Mix vegetables and spaghetti together.
Sprinkle 1/2 to 3/4 bottle of salad seasoning and mix.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 bottle of Italian seasoning to pasta and vegetables.
You can chill overnight or eat it right away.
Either way, it's delicious.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: In microwave or on stove top, melt margarine and add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add milk and boil.
Stir until thick.
Add the grated cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add salt, pepper and mustard.

title: bacon cheese potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes 1/2-inch thick and layer in glass dish.
Mix cooking oil, seasoned salt, pepper and salt together.
Pour mixture over potatoes and bake at 375° until tender.
When done, crumble bacon and cheese over top of potatoes.
Top with sour cream.

title: fried peanuts
directions: Heat 1/2-inch Mazola corn oil in cast-iron pan until hot.
Put in hulled peanuts and reduce heat.
When peanuts begin to brown, take out and place on pan lined with wax paper.
Salt peanuts. Will get browner as they cool.
Let cool completely and store in tin can with seal.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Pour apples in large bowl.
Break eggs over apples; add other ingredients and mix.
Bake in greased baking dish at 325° for 1 hour or in a Bundt pan for 1 hour.

title: spiced yogurt dressing
directions: In a small bowl, whisk yogurt, lemon juice, oil, cumin, ginger and garlic until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Dressing will keep, covered in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.

title: one minute icing
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cocoa and milk together.
Add melted margarine.
Stir until it comes to a rolling boil.
Boil 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat until mixture starts to thicken.
Add vanilla and continue to beat until ready to spread on cake.

title: kelli's favorite sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix ingredients. Roll into balls; flatten with bottom of glass that has been dipped into colored sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 4 layers. Cool and frost.

title: marinade for beef, pork or chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 40 seconds. Makes 3 1/2 cups marinade. Marinate meat all day before cooking.

title: seafood marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place fish fillets or raw shrimp in a bowl and cover with marinade.
Let stand at room temperature for at least 30 minutes.
Place shrimp or fish in a broiling pan 5 to 6 inches from the heat.
Broil until done and occasionally baste with marinade.

title: beef tips
directions: Cut beef into bite-size pieces.
Mix with soups and water. Cook tender enough to cut with a fork.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: easter bread basket
directions: Prepare hot roll mix as directed on package, except use 1 1/2 cups water for the 2 boxes of mix; use 4 eggs and 6 tablespoons sugar (omit margarine).
Let rise; punch down.
Divide dough into thirds.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1/4 cup shortening and egg. Mix well.
Add sugar, salt and 3 1/2 cups of the flour.
Mix well.
Add the remaining 3 1/2 cups of flour.
Mix well.
Let rise until double.
Make into rolls.
Place in 2 (9 x 13-inch) greased pans or 1 (12 x 18-inch) pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 30 rolls.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix well with sausage and biscuit mix and sauce.
Shape into balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Cut up margarine and cheese together; melt in microwave. Mix sugar, pecans and cocoa together. Stir in cheese, margarine and vanilla. Add coconut, if desired.
Half of this recipe makes a lot.

title: home-made play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook mixture over low heat until it thickens and rolls into a ball.
Cool and knead.
Put in airtight container or Ziploc bag.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese on each slice ham.
Place 1 green onion on and roll up tightly.
Snip off top of onion.
Slice into desired thickness.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add coconut and flour; beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread mixture in a well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Set aside to cool and then enjoy!

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Cut cake in half.
Spread bottom half with icing and then put top half back on.
Top with icing, then add cherry pie filling. Serve.

title: good dried beans
directions: Place beans in large pot with 12 cups water.
Add all ingredients except parsley and olives.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 3 hours.
Five minutes before beans are finished, add parsley, olives, salt and pepper to taste.
Can be served over cooked white rice.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Melt butter and pour over oats.
Combine all dry ingredients and add to oat mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and blend. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on an ungreased foil-covered cookie sheet.
Cookies will come off easily when cool.

title: waffles
directions: Bake according to package directions.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding over pineapple.
Stir in other ingredients. Place in oblong dish.
Chill overnight.
Serves 10.

title: stuffed manicotti(for two)
directions: Cook manicotti according to the package directions for 10 minutes (exactly) and drain.
Cool in a single layer to keep the spinach, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, egg, garlic powder and pepper.
Stuff all this mixture into the manicotti.

title: crab cake recipe
directions: Beat the egg in a bowl.
Trim the crusts from the bread and break the slices into small pieces.
Add these pieces to the egg. Mix in the mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, Chesapeake seasoning and parsley; beat well.
Place the crab meat in a bowl and pour the egg mixture over the top.
Gently toss or fold the ingredients together, taking care not to break up the lumps of crab meat.
Form the cakes by hand into patties, about 3-inches around and 3/4-inch thick.
The shape should be like a cookie, not like a meatball or golf ball.
Place the cakes in the refrigerator for at least 45 minutes before cooking.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup and sour cream.
Reserve 1 cup.
Add chicken to soup/sour cream mixture.
Mix together in medium bowl chilies and cheese.
Place chicken mixture in center of each tortilla. Top with cheese/chili mixture, then fold.
Place tortillas in baking dish, fold side down. Pour remaining soup mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with black olives and more cheese if desired.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over chicken and apples, mixing lightly. Combine remaining ingredients, using only enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Add chicken and apples and toss together lightly.
Serve cold.

title: creamy peanut butter pie
directions: Mix with mixer the peanut butter and cream cheese; add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread half of mixture on crust and half of fudge topping, then layer rest of mixture. Cover and freeze 6 hours.
Let pie stand at room temperature before serving for 15 minutes.
Drizzle top of pie with fudge topping and nuts before serving, if you desire.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Butter a large baking sheet.
In microwaveproof bowl, combine peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High until mixture bubbles vigorously, about 6 minutes.
Remove mixture from microwave and stir in butter and vanilla.
Return to microwave and cook on High until candy turns light gold color, about three minutes.
Remove bowl from microwave.
Working quickly, add baking soda to candy mixture and stir briskly (mixture will foam up). Immediately pour out onto prepared baking sheet.
Shake baking sheet from side to side to spread brittle as thinly as possible. Let stand until cold and hard, about 2 hours.
Break brittle into pieces.
Store in airtight container at room temperature for up to one month.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to box directions.
Beat in softened cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and fold in.
Make layers of wafers, pudding and bananas, continue until all pudding is used.
Garnish top with left over vanilla wafers.

title: scotch cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
In saucepan, put oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to boil.
Pour into flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Bake in greased and floured pan, 13 x 9 x 12-inch at 375°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add flour and oatmeal last.
Roll into little balls.
Put on cookie sheet; bake until cookies are lightly browned.
Will make about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: lamb stew
directions: Cut lamb in
1-inch square pieces; dredge lamb in flour well. Heat cooking oil in frypan and brown lamb well.
Season with salt and
pepper.
Cover
with
water
and
simmer
until nearly tender, about
1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables except tomatoes and simmer
minutes
longer or until tender.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes longer; mix a little flour with water to a smooth
paste.
Add enough to the liquid to thicken slightly. Serves 5 to 7.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Blend in milk. Combine dry ingredients; mix by hand into the first mixture.
Fold in blueberries very gently.

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix tomato paste and olive oil together.
Brush on steaks. Coat the steaks with garlic powder, Italian seasoning and lemon and pepper.
Place in refrigerator for one hour, then grill steaks as usual.
You may add more lemon and pepper as you grill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine the squash and milk; crumble in cornbread.
Saute the onions, celery and bell pepper.
Add soup, sage, salt and pepper. Mix with squash mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry marvel pie
directions: Cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Whip cream until it stands in peaks; fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Add lemon juice to cherries and mix; pout into shell.
Chill 3 hours.

title: crispie candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup; bring to rolling boil.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add cereal.
Spread in pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
